  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"aatrox","win":["Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Aatrox","Aatrox","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is Aatrox's window: once he has Q1-Q2-Q3 plus E dash, he can chain sweet-spots and heal off his W-chained damage while your Q Bloodlust heals stay small. Sidestep the third Q's slam edge and don't trade into a full combo."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R Undying Rage flips the fight. Aatrox's whole kill pattern relies on executing you low, but if you pop Undying Rage you survive his combo, top your Fury bar off crits, and Q-heal back to full while his W and E are down."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With early crit (IE/Collector or Kraken tempo) your DPS outpaces his sustain. He can't kite you forever once E Spinning Slash lets you stick, and his revive passive comes up too rarely to save him in a straight duel."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late you win extended fights hard: crit stacking plus double R availability means he cannot burst you before Undying Rage, and you split-push faster than he can answer."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 6 with Undying Rage up before committing","Dodge his third Q slam edge and E knock-up","Stack crit and Fury to spin-crit through his revive"],"foe":["Land the sweet-spot edge of all three Q casts","Chain W drag-in plus E to lock a full combo","Kill you before 6 or bait your R then all-in"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 favour you: before Aatrox has his Q chain and E online he has no reliable poke or heal, so you can walk up, Q for the crit-heal, and win short auto trades while he only has one Q ready.","mid":"Levels 3-6 are Aatrox's spot. With all three Q casts, E dash and W chain he sweet-spots you, heals off the damage and looks to execute you low before your R exists; play the wave, dodge Q edges, and don't trade into his full combo until you hit 6.","late":"Once you have Undying Rage and first-item crit the matchup swings back to you: R negates his kill combo, crit-Q heals refill you instantly, and his passive revive comes up far too slowly to survive your sustained spin-crit DPS.","whys":["Level 1 is yours because Aatrox has only one Q and no heal chain, so your Q-heal wins the short trade.","Level 2 stays yours since he still lacks E and full Q access while you already threaten crit autos.","Level 3 flips to Aatrox once his three-Q chain plus E dash lets him sweet-spot and out-heal you.","Levels 4-5 remain Aatrox's as his combo and W drag-in can execute you before your R exists.","Level 6 is yours because Undying Rage survives his full combo and lets you crit-heal back to full.","First item is yours as crit DPS outpaces his sustain and his revive comes up too rarely.","With 2+ items you win extended duels outright, negating his burst with R before he can kill you."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"akali","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Skill","Akali","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Roughly even and skill-dependent: Akali's Q Five Point Strike pokes and heals, and her W Twilight Shroud gives her a smoke screen to reset trades. Punish her when W is down, but respect the mana-cheap Q poke that chips you between crits."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her R Perfect Execution comes online but so does your Undying Rage. When she dashes in to burst you, pop R, ride out the damage, and crit-Q back up; she blows her whole combo and cooldowns for nothing while you stay on her."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With early crit your autos plus E Spinning Slash outrange her escape once her Shroud and dashes are on cooldown. Bait the W, then all-in; she can't kite a crit Tryndamere who has R as insurance."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late you dominate: double R availability and crit stacking mean her assassin burst can't kill through Undying Rage, and you win the split and any even-numbers skirmish."}],"wants":{"you":["Hit level 6 so R covers her all-in","Force out W Twilight Shroud, then commit","Stack crit and use E to stick through her dashes"],"foe":["Poke you down with cheap Q Five Point Strike","Use W Shroud to dodge your commit and reset","Burst you with R Perfect Execution before your R is up"]},"early":"Level 1 is yours: Akali has only Q and no Shroud or mobility, so you can walk up and win the auto-Q trade before her poke pattern exists. Take the short trades while she's a sitting target.","mid":"Levels 2-5 are skill-dependent and roughly even. Akali's Q pokes and heals cheaply and her W smoke screen lets her dodge your commits and reset, so trades hinge on whether you catch her without Shroud; at level 6 her R burst threatens you before yours reliably answers.","late":"From your own level 6 onward the matchup is yours: Undying Rage negates her Perfect Execution burst, crit-Q heals refill you as she blows her combo, and with first-item crit plus E you stick through her dashes and out-DPS her once Shroud is down.","whys":["Level 1 is yours because Akali has only Q and no Shroud, so your auto-Q trade wins outright.","Level 2 is even and skill-based as her cheap Q poke starts trading with your crits.","Levels 3-5 stay skill-dependent since W Twilight Shroud lets her reset and dodge your commits.","Levels 4-5 tip to Akali as her Q sustain and Shroud out-pace you before your R exists.","Level 6 is yours because Undying Rage survives her R burst and lets you crit back to full.","First item is yours as crit DPS plus E outpaces her escape once Shroud is down.","With 2+ items you win outright, negating her assassin burst with R in every skirmish."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"akshan","win":["Skill","Akshan","Skill","Tryndamere","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Level 2-3 is Akshan's poke window: his Q Avengerang and passive Dirty Fighting shield let him trade autos and back off. Once you hit level 4 and get E Spinning Slash you can close the gap and turn his poke into a losing melee trade."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Skill-based at 6: his R Comeuppance is a long-charge execute, but you can pop Undying Rage to eat it, or E out of the channel. Don't sit still in his ult range when your own R is down."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With crit online you overwhelm him. Bait his E Heroic Swing grapple, then all-in; once his dash is on cooldown he has no escape from a crit Tryndamere and you shred his squishy build."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late you win any duel: he's a fragile marksman, so double R plus crit means you delete him before Comeuppance finishes charging."}],"wants":{"you":["Get E level 4 to close his poke range","Bait out E Heroic Swing, then commit","Stack crit to delete his squishy build"],"foe":["Poke with Q Avengerang and passive shield","Kite with E Heroic Swing grapple","Land a fully charged R Comeuppance execute"]},"early":"Level 1 is skill-dependent and roughly even, but by level 2-3 Akshan's Q Avengerang poke plus his passive shield let him win ranged trades and back off before you can answer. Farm safely and avoid extended trades until you have your gap-closer.","mid":"Once you hit level 4 and E Spinning Slash the matchup swings to you: you close his poke range and turn every trade into melee where crit-Q beats his kit. Level 6 is skill-based since his R Comeuppance can execute you when your R is down, so respect its range and E out of the channel.","late":"With first-item crit and beyond you dominate: Akshan is a squishy marksman, so once you bait his E grapple you all-in and delete him, and double Undying Rage plus crit means you kill him before Comeuppance ever charges.","whys":["Level 1 is even and skill-based before either champ has a real trade pattern.","Level 2 is Akshan's as his Q poke and passive shield win the ranged trade.","Level 3 is skill-dependent while you look to farm toward your gap-closer.","Levels 4-5 are yours once E Spinning Slash closes his range into a losing melee trade.","Level 6 is skill-based since his R Comeuppance can execute you while your R is down.","First item is yours as crit lets you all-in and delete his squishy build after his E.","With 2+ items you win outright, killing him before Comeuppance finishes charging."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"ambessa","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Skill","Ambessa","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ambessa's power spot: with her W Repudiation counter-window and her Q Cunning Sweep chains plus E dashes she can chain-engage and punish your commits. Don't auto into her W parry, and respect the double-dash gap close when your E is down."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R Undying Rage answers her R Public Execution lockdown. When she chains in to burst you, pop R, survive the combo, and crit-Q back up while her dashes and W are spent."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With crit online your sustained DPS beats her burst-reliant kit. Once her E dashes and W parry are down she has no way to peel a crit Tryndamere, and E Spinning Slash keeps you glued to her."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late you win extended duels: crit stacking plus double R means her combo can't kill through Undying Rage, and you out-split and out-skirmish her."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 6 so R covers her all-in","Avoid auto-attacking into her W parry window","Stack crit and use E to stick past her dashes"],"foe":["Chain Q Cunning Sweep and E dashes to engage","Bait and parry your commit with W Repudiation","Lock you with R Public Execution and burst"]},"early":"Level 1 is yours: before Ambessa has her Q chains, W parry and E dashes online she has no engage or counter, so you can walk up, Q for the crit-heal and win the short auto trade. Take that early tempo before she spikes.","mid":"Levels 2-5 tip toward Ambessa. Her Q Cunning Sweep chains, double E dashes and W Repudiation counter-window let her engage on her terms and punish your commits, and before your R exists her burst can kill you; play the wave and dodge her W parry until you hit 6.","late":"From your level 6 on the matchup is yours: Undying Rage negates her R Public Execution burst, crit-Q refills you as she spends her dashes and parry, and with first-item crit plus E you glue to her and out-DPS her burst-reliant kit in every extended fight.","whys":["Level 1 is yours because Ambessa lacks her chains and parry, so your Q-heal wins the trade.","Level 2 is skill-based as she starts assembling her Q and dash pattern.","Levels 3-5 tip to Ambessa once her Q chains, E dashes and W parry let her engage and punish.","Levels 4-5 stay Ambessa's as her burst can kill you before your R exists.","Level 6 is yours because Undying Rage survives her R lockdown and you crit back to full.","First item is yours as crit DPS beats her burst kit once dashes and W are down.","With 2+ items you win extended duels, negating her combo with R every skirmish."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"aurora","win":["Skill","Tryndamere","Skill","Skill","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Skill-based poke phase: Aurora's Q Twofold Hunt and W Spirit Abjuration blink let her chip you and dodge your commit. Punish the moment her W is on cooldown, and don't eat free Q double-hits while walking up to farm."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her R Between Worlds zones the fight, but it's a terrain ult, not burst; at 6 things stay skill-based since you can E Spinning Slash out of the wall and Undying Rage covers her damage if she commits."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With crit online you outrange her escape once W blink is down. Bait the W, then all-in with E; a fragile mage can't survive a crit Tryndamere who has R as insurance."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late you dominate any duel: double R and crit stacking mean her poke and zone can't kill you, and you delete her the moment you reach her."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait out W Spirit Abjuration, then commit","Use E to escape her R Between Worlds wall","Stack crit to delete her squishy build"],"foe":["Poke with Q Twofold Hunt double-hits","Blink your commit away with W Abjuration","Zone and split you with R Between Worlds"]},"early":"Level 1 is skill-dependent and roughly even, but level 2 is a clean spot for you: before Aurora has her W blink up she can't escape, so you can walk up, Q for the crit-heal and win the short trade. Take that window before her kit comes online.","mid":"Levels 3-6 are skill-based. Aurora's Q double-hit poke and W Spirit Abjuration blink let her chip you and dodge your commits, so trades hinge on catching her without W; her R Between Worlds zones rather than bursts, and Undying Rage plus E out of the wall keeps you safe when she commits.","late":"With first-item crit and beyond you take over: bait her W blink, all-in with E and delete her fragile build, and double Undying Rage plus crit means her poke and zone can never kill you before you reach and shred her.","whys":["Level 1 is even and skill-based before either champ has a trade pattern.","Level 2 is yours because Aurora lacks her W blink, so your crit-Q trade wins outright.","Level 3 is skill-based as her Q poke and W blink start dodging your commits.","Levels 4-5 stay skill-dependent while she pokes and you look to catch her without W.","Level 6 is skill-based since her R zones rather than bursts and your R covers her damage.","First item is yours as crit plus E lets you all-in and delete her once W is down.","With 2+ items you win outright, her poke and zone unable to kill through your R."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"camille","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Skill-based mid-window: Camille's Q Precision Protocol double-hit and E Hookshot wall-dash let her burst-trade and disengage. Punish her when E is down, and don't stand next to walls where her Hookshot stun lands cleanly."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R Undying Rage beats her R Hextech Ultimatum isolation. When she ults to lock you 1v1, pop Undying Rage, ride out her Q burst, and crit-Q back up while her E and W shield are spent."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With crit you overwhelm her sustained trades. Once E Hookshot is down she has no escape, and your own E Spinning Slash keeps you glued while her true-damage Q can't out-DPS your crits."},{"when":"Late","text":"Skill-based late but favoured: her R can catch you if you're careless, yet double Undying Rage plus crit means she can't finish you inside the arena, and you win most numbers fights and the split."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach 6 so R covers her Ultimatum lockdown","Force out E Hookshot before committing","Stay off walls to deny her E stun angle"],"foe":["Burst-trade with Q Precision Protocol true damage","Engage or escape with E Hookshot wall-dash","Isolate you with R Hextech Ultimatum"]},"early":"Level 1 is yours: before Camille has her Q charge, E Hookshot and W shield she has no burst or engage, so you can walk up, Q for the crit-heal and win the short auto trade. Grab that early tempo before her kit spikes.","mid":"Levels 2-3 are skill-based as her Q double-hit and E Hookshot come online for burst-trades and disengage, but from level 4 you swing ahead: E Spinning Slash lets you stick, crit-Q out-heals her Q, and at 6 Undying Rage negates her R isolation combo. Play around baiting her Hookshot.","late":"Item phase is strongly yours through first item, tipping to skill-based with two items only because her R can catch a careless step. Even then double Undying Rage plus crit means she can't kill you inside Hextech Ultimatum, and you win the split and most skirmishes.","whys":["Level 1 is yours because Camille lacks her burst and Hookshot, so your Q-heal wins the trade.","Level 2 is skill-based as her Q and E come online for burst-trades and disengage.","Level 3 stays skill-dependent while she trades and you look to catch her without E.","Levels 4-5 are yours once E lets you stick and crit-Q out-heals her Q burst.","Level 6 is yours because Undying Rage negates her R isolation combo and you crit back up.","First item is yours as crit overwhelms her sustained trades once Hookshot is down.","With 2+ items it's skill-based since her R can catch a careless step, but your R still saves you."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"cassiopeia","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Cassiopeia","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Cassiopeia's lane: her Q Noxious Blast and W Miasma poison zone chip you constantly and her E Twin Fang resets on poisoned targets for heavy sustained DPS. Don't walk through her W puddle to engage, and time your all-in for when W is on cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Skill-based at 6 but tense: her R Petrifying Gaze faces you down, so approach from an angle or bait it, and if she lands it you can pop Undying Rage to survive the follow-up E poison DPS."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With crit online you flip it: once you dodge her W and reach her, E Spinning Slash sticks and a fragile mage melts to crit autos before her Twin Fang can out-sustain the burst."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late you dominate any duel: double R and crit stacking mean her poison DPS can't kill through Undying Rage, and you delete her the instant you close the gap."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge her W Miasma puddle when engaging","Bait or side-angle her R Petrifying Gaze","Stack crit and use E to reach and delete her"],"foe":["Chip you with Q Noxious Blast and W Miasma poison","Sustain with E Twin Fang resets on poisoned targets","Face-check you with R Petrifying Gaze then poison-DPS"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are skill-dependent but lean on Cassiopeia's poison zoning: her Q Noxious Blast and W Miasma chip you every time you step to farm, and her E Twin Fang resets keep her sustained. Play for CS, sidestep her skillshots and avoid extended trades while her kit outranges you.","mid":"Level 4 is Cassiopeia's clear spot as her full poison rotation and W puddle deny your approach, and at level 6 her R Petrifying Gaze can lock you for a poison burst; keep it skill-based by angling around her ult and Undying Rage covers the follow-up if she lands it.","late":"From first item on the matchup is yours: once you dodge her W and reach her with E, a squishy mage melts to crit autos before Twin Fang can out-heal the burst, and with two items plus double Undying Rage her poison DPS can never kill you before you delete her.","whys":["Level 1 is skill-based as her poison poke starts but neither champ has a kill threat.","Level 2 stays skill-dependent while her Q and W chip you at farm range.","Level 3 is skill-based as her E Twin Fang sustain builds but you can still dodge and farm.","Level 4 is Cassiopeia's once her full poison rotation and W puddle deny your approach.","Level 6 is skill-based since angling around R Petrifying Gaze and your own R keep you alive.","First item is yours as crit autos melt her squishy build once you reach her past W.","With 2+ items you win outright, her poison DPS unable to kill through Undying Rage."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"chogath","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Cho'Gath's Rupture (Q) and Vorpal Spikes (E) let him farm and poke safely, but with Fury built you can walk up between Q casts and Bloodlust-heal the spike damage back. Bait his Rupture, dodge it, then E in for a crit trade while it's on cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Cho'Gath hits 6 wanting Feast (R) as an execute, but with Undying Rage up you're immune to it as an execute during ghost form. Play for a level-6 all-in: full Fury, E in, W to slow his escape, and burst him before he can Rupture-Scream you off."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first crit item (Collector or Kraken) massively out-scales his slow farming start. Cho'Gath needs stacks and levels; you need only a lead. Perma-shove, roam, and deny his Feast stacks by never dying to it."},{"when":"Late","text":"A stacked Cho'Gath is tanky, but Tryndamere shreds tanks with crit + on-hit and your R negates his Feast execute. Bring Lord Dominik's; W his flash/escape and Q through the fight. You win extended duels once he can't one-shot you."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Rupture then E-crit during its cooldown","Full Fury before any all-in","Bait Feast then survive it with R active"],"foe":["Land Rupture to zone you off the wave","Stack Feast size and health to become unkillable","Poke you down with Vorpal Spikes while you last-hit"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are even and farm-focused: Cho'Gath just wants to spike Vorpal Spikes and stack, while you build Fury and dodge Rupture. Neither of you has a real all-in window yet, so respect his Q range and last-hit carefully.","mid":"Through levels 3-6 it stays a skill matchup around dodging Rupture. If you eat his Q you take a bad trade; if you dodge it you get a free E-in crit while it's down. His level-6 Feast is scary but telegraphed, and once you hit 6 your Undying Rage flips the all-in in your favor.","late":"From your first item onward you pull ahead hard. Crit scaling beats his slow-stacking value pattern, and R immunity to the Feast execute means his single biggest threat is neutralized. Perma-shove, deny stacks, and duel him once he can't burst you.","whys":["Level 1 is even farming with no kill pressure either way.","Level 2 stays skill-based as both sides just push toward their spikes.","Level 3 is a dodge-Rupture skill check with no clear favorite.","Levels 4-5 remain even, decided by whether you dodge his Q pokes.","At 6 your Undying Rage negates the Feast execute, flipping the all-in to you.","Your first crit item out-scales his slow stacking start, so you're ahead.","With items your crit shreds his tankiness while R denies his execute, keeping you favored."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"darius","win":["Skill","Skill","Darius","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Level 3 belongs to Darius: with Decimate (Q), Crippling Strike (W) and the Apprehend (E) pull online he wins any short trade and can pull you into his outer-Q sweet spot for bleed stacks. Don't sit in his Q range at 3-5; only trade when his E is on cooldown, then E in, Q crit, and disengage before he pulls."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your Undying Rage completely negates Noxian Guillotine (R). Darius wants 5 bleed stacks then a reset execute, but your R makes you unkillable through the execute window and Bloodlust heals the stacks off. At 6 you flip the lane: bait his E, pop R if needed, and duel him with Fury."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With a crit item and level lead you out-duel him. Kite his W slow with E and W his own movement, heal bleed with Bloodlust, and never let him land the outer edge of Decimate. His all-in relies on your death to reset R cooldown; deny it with your ult."},{"when":"Late","text":"Tryndamere scales past Darius once crit and Lord Dominik's come online. His R execute is dead against your Undying Rage, so extended fights favor you. Split-push, force him to answer, and win the 1v1 he can no longer close with Guillotine."}],"wants":{"you":["Trade only when his Apprehend (E) is down","Pop R to survive his Guillotine execute","Heal bleed stacks with Bloodlust between trades"],"foe":["Land outer-edge Decimate for max bleed and heal","Pull you in with E then Crippling Strike","Hit 5 stacks and reset with Noxian Guillotine"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are a skill matchup: neither of you has a full combo, so respect his Q and just farm while building Fury. Avoid standing at the outer edge of his Decimate where the healing and bleed are strongest, and don't give him an early E pull with the wave.","mid":"Level 3 is Darius's window once E, W and Q are all up and he can pull-combo you for stacks. Play around his Apprehend cooldown through 4-5 and only commit when it's down. The moment you hit 6, Undying Rage negates his Guillotine execute and the all-in swings to you.","late":"From your first item on you're the better duelist. R hard-counters his reset-execute pattern, Bloodlust washes off bleed, and crit scaling shreds him. Split-push, deny his stacks, and take the 1v1 he can no longer finish.","whys":["Level 1 is even, just farming and respecting Q range.","Level 2 stays skill-based with no full combo online for either.","At 3 Darius's E-pull combo and bleed stacking make him the clear favorite.","By 4-5 your Fury trades and heal let you flip the short exchanges to your side.","At 6 Undying Rage negates his Guillotine execute, handing you the all-in.","Your first crit item and lead out-duel his stacking kit.","Late, R kills his reset-execute pattern and crit scaling shreds him, so you're favored."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"drmundo","win":["Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Mundo's only early threat is Infected Bonesaw (Q) poke, but with Fury built you Bloodlust-heal it back instantly. He can't punish you at all: E in, Q crit, W to slow his low-mobility escape, and walk out. Deny his cleaver by juking behind minions and you control every trade."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Mundo's Maximum Dosage (R) gives huge sustain and move speed, but it doesn't save him from a committed Tryndamere all-in. With full Fury and Undying Rage you out-heal his regen and crit through his tankiness. Force fights while his R is down and punish his weak wave clear."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first crit item plus Lord Dominik's/Kraken shreds his stacked health. Mundo is a slow-scaling tank with no burst; you're a crit duelist who eats tanks. Perma-shove, roam for kills, and 1v1 him whenever you like — he simply can't kill you."},{"when":"Late","text":"Even a fully built Mundo loses the 1v1 to Tryndamere with %HP shred. Your R makes you unkillable through his sustain windows and crit + on-hit melts his health bar. Split-push and take every duel; this is one of your cleanest tank matchups."}],"wants":{"you":["Heal his cleaver poke off with Bloodlust","E in and W his low-mobility escape","Buy %HP shred to melt his stacked health"],"foe":["Poke with Infected Bonesaw from range","Stack health and scale into the late game","Pop R sustain to survive a trade"]},"early":"You control levels 1-2 outright. Mundo's only tool is his cleaver poke, and with Fury you heal it right back while he has no way to punish your approach. Farm freely, dodge his Q, and set up early E-in crit trades whenever he steps up.","mid":"Through 3-6 you dominate. His low mobility means your W slow and E gap-close lock him down, and Bloodlust out-sustains his passive regen. His level-6 R gives sustain but no kill threat, so keep forcing trades and shoving him under tower.","late":"This stays in your favor all game. Crit scaling with %HP shred eats his stacked health, and Undying Rage negates any window his sustain gives him. Split-push, deny his farm, and take the free 1v1 whenever he shows.","whys":["Level 1 you dominate — he can only poke and you heal it off.","Level 2 stays yours with no punish available to his kit.","At 3 your E-in W-slow crit trades control the lane against his low mobility.","By 4-5 Bloodlust out-sustains his regen and you keep winning trades.","At 6 his R gives sustain but no kill threat, so you're still ahead.","Your first crit item and %HP shred out-scale his slow tank stacking.","Late, crit shred plus R immunity makes the 1v1 permanently yours."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"fiora","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Skill","Fiora"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You out-trade Fiora early: with Fury and Bloodlust you win the raw stat exchange before her Riposte (W) window matters. E in, Q crit, and W to slow her Lunge (Q) reposition. Just respect her Riposte — bait it out or trade after it's down, because it parries and stuns your committed hit."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your Undying Rage beats her Grand Challenge (R) execute — she can't finish you through ghost form and Bloodlust heals her passive vitals damage. At 6 you hold the all-in edge: force fights while her W is on cooldown and burst her before she cycles vital procs."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Fiora's item spike (Hullbreaker/Shojin) turns her into a duel monster, so the lane tightens back to skill. Keep trading around her Riposte cooldown and don't let her free-hit your vitals. You're still fine but she's online now."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game flips to Fiora: her true-damage vitals and Riposte parry make her the premier 1v1 duelist, and she can proc your side-vitals faster than you can crit her down. Avoid isolated splits against a fed Fiora; group and use R only to survive, then disengage rather than committing a losing extended duel."}],"wants":{"you":["Trade after her Riposte (W) is down","E-in W-slow to punish her Lunge reposition","All-in at 6 while her W is on cooldown"],"foe":["Parry your committed crit with Riposte","Proc all four vitals for the true-damage burst","Reach her item spike and out-duel you late"]},"early":"Level 1 is yours — raw Fury stats beat her before any Riposte matters. Level 2 evens out as she gets her Lunge-vital pattern going, so trade carefully and always respect her W parry, which will stun you if you commit a crit into it.","mid":"Levels 3-6 favor you. Your E-in, Q-crit, W-slow trade wins around her Riposte cooldown, and at 6 Undying Rage negates her Grand Challenge execute while Bloodlust heals off her vital damage. Force fights when her W is down and you hold the edge.","late":"The matchup inverts with items. Once Fiora hits her first spike the lane returns to skill, and by 2+ items her true-damage vitals and parry make her the better duelist. Don't feed an isolated split; group up and treat your R as an escape, not a commit.","whys":["Level 1 your raw Fury stats out-trade her before Riposte matters.","Level 2 evens out as her Lunge-vital poke pattern comes online.","At 3 your E-in W-slow crit trade wins around her Riposte cooldown.","By 4-5 you keep out-trading her when her parry is down.","At 6 Undying Rage negates her Grand Challenge execute, keeping the all-in yours.","Her first item spike turns her into a duelist and levels the lane to skill.","With 2+ items her true-damage vitals and parry out-duel you, so she's favored."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"galio","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Skill","Galio","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Galio's Winds of War (Q) poke and Shield of Durand (W) damage-reduction make levels 4-5 his window — he can zone you and tank your trades behind W. Don't walk into his Q double-tornado; wait for W to be down, then E in and Q crit before he can charge Durand's taunt."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Galio's ult is a global roam tool, not a lane-kill button, so at 6 the lane control swings back to you. With full Fury and Undying Rage you all-in through his W and Justice Punch (E) knock-up. Track when his R is used to roam and punish the side lane before he returns."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first crit item out-scales his utility-mage build. Galio wants to scale for teamfights; you want to snowball the side lane. Perma-shove so his roams cost him CS, and 1v1 him whenever his W damage-reduction is on cooldown."},{"when":"Late","text":"Tryndamere out-duels a utility Galio 1v1 all game — his damage is teamfight-oriented, not single-target. Crit + shred beats his tankiness, and R covers his E-Q knock-up combo. Split-push and force him to choose between defending and grouping."}],"wants":{"you":["Trade when his Shield of Durand (W) is down","All-in at 6 while he lacks a lane-kill ult","Perma-shove to punish his roam-focused ult"],"foe":["Poke with double Winds of War (Q)","Tank trades behind W damage reduction","Land E-Q knock-up to zone or set a gank"]},"early":"Level 1 is yours with raw Fury stats. From level 2 into 3 it evens out as his Q poke and W come online and he can trade tankily, so pick your moments and don't eat the double-tornado center.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are Galio's window — his Q zoning and W damage reduction let him win trades and control the wave. Respect his taunt setup and only commit when W is down. At 6 the lane swings back to you: his ult is a roam tool, not a duel button, and your Undying Rage all-in beats his kit.","late":"You pull ahead from your first item on. Crit scaling out-values his utility build, R covers his knock-up combo, and he can't 1v1 you. Perma-shove to punish roams, split-push, and force him into losing side-lane duels.","whys":["Level 1 your raw Fury stats out-trade him.","Level 2 evens as his Q poke and W come online.","Level 3 stays skill-based with both able to trade.","At 4-5 his W damage reduction and Q zoning give him the trade edge.","At 6 his ult only roams, so your Undying Rage all-in retakes the lane.","Your first crit item out-scales his utility-mage build.","Late, crit shred and R coverage make the 1v1 permanently yours."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"gangplank","win":["Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You dominate early: Gangplank is squishy and his Parrrley (Q) poke is easy to heal with Bloodlust once you have Fury. E in, Q crit, W to slow, and he can't fight back before items. Kick his barrels early — one melee hit detonates them — to deny his combo and force bad trades."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Gangplank's Cannon Barrage (R) is global map pressure, not a lane duel tool, so at 6 you still hold the all-in. With full Fury and Undying Rage you kill him before he can chain barrels. Keep detonating his kegs and punish him while his crit-item power spike hasn't landed yet."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is where it flips: Gangplank's first spike (Sheen/Essence Reaver + Trinity) turns his barrels and empowered Q into massive burst that can chunk you from range and self-heal his crit build. He out-ranges your all-in now — respect keg zones and stop diving him freely."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game favors Gangplank: stacked barrels detonate for huge AoE crit damage that beats your engage range, and his Cannon Barrage plus global gold snowball out-scale you. Don't chase him into keg fields; group with your team, and use R only to survive the barrel burst, not to force a losing extended fight."}],"wants":{"you":["Detonate his barrels with a melee hit before they chain","Trade early while he's squishy and pre-item","All-in at 6 before his crit spike lands"],"foe":["Chain 3 barrels for a burst crit combo","Reach his Trinity/crit item spike to out-range you","Snowball global gold with Cannon Barrage"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are all yours. Gangplank is fragile before items and his only tool is Q poke, which you heal off with Bloodlust. E in for crit trades, W to stick, and detonate his barrels with a single melee hit so he never gets his combo online.","mid":"Through levels 4-6 you stay ahead. Keep punishing his squishy pre-item body and denying kegs, and remember his level-6 ult only pressures the map — it doesn't win the lane duel. All-in him before his first crit item lands and Undying Rage seals any commit.","late":"The lane inverts at his first item. Trinity plus a crit component turns barrel chains into ranged burst that beats your engage, and his global gold and Cannon Barrage out-scale you. Stop diving keg fields, group up, and treat R as survival rather than a commit into his zone.","whys":["Level 1 you dominate his squishy pre-item body.","Level 2 stays yours as you heal his Q poke and punish him.","Level 3 you control trades with E-in crits and keg denial.","By 4-5 he's still fragile and you keep winning trades.","At 6 his ult only pressures the map, so your all-in still wins.","At his first item, barrel-Q burst out-ranges your all-in and flips the lane.","Late, stacked-keg AoE crit and global snowball out-scale you, so he's favored."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"garen","win":["Skill","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once you have Fury you out-trade Garen: his Decisive Strike (Q) silence-hit is his only real burst, so bait it, then E in and Q crit while it's on cooldown. Bloodlust heals through his Judgment (E) spin, and W slows him out of it. Trade after his Q, not into it."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Garen's Demacian Justice (R) is a true-damage execute on low targets, but Undying Rage makes you immune to it during ghost form. He wants to Q-silence, E-spin, then R your low HP — but your R denies the finish and Bloodlust refills. At 6 you clearly win the all-in."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your crit item out-scales his bruiser build. Garen has no sustained damage once his E spin is healed off, while your crits shred him. Perma-shove, deny his passive regen by staying on him, and 1v1 whenever his Q is down."},{"when":"Late","text":"Tryndamere beats Garen 1v1 all game once crit and Lord Dominik's land. His R execute is negated by Undying Rage and your %HP shred eats his tank stats. Split-push freely — he can't kill you and can't match your side-lane pressure."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait his Decisive Strike (Q) then E-crit while it's down","Heal his Judgment (E) spin off with Bloodlust","Pop R to deny his Demacian Justice execute"],"foe":["Land the Q silence to stop your abilities","Spin E while you're stuck in his damage","Execute you low with Demacian Justice (R)"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are a skill matchup around his Decisive Strike. If you eat the Q silence into his E spin you take a bad trade; if you dodge or bait the Q you're fine. Just farm, build Fury, and don't get silenced while committed.","mid":"From level 3 on you take over. Your E-in, Q-crit, W-slow trade wins around his Q cooldown, Bloodlust heals through his spin, and at 6 Undying Rage negates his Demacian Justice execute. Force fights whenever his silence is down and you hold the edge.","late":"You stay ahead all game. Crit scaling with %HP shred beats his bruiser stats, and R hard-counters his execute finish. Perma-shove, deny his passive regen by sticking to him, and take the free split-push 1v1.","whys":["Level 1 is even, a skill check around his Q silence.","Level 2 stays skill-based before you have full Fury.","At 3 your E-in crit trade wins around his Decisive Strike cooldown.","By 4-5 Bloodlust heals his spin off and you keep out-trading him.","At 6 Undying Rage negates his Demacian Justice execute, giving you the all-in.","Your first crit item out-scales his bruiser build.","Late, crit shred plus R immunity make the 1v1 permanently yours."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"gnar","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Gnar","Tryndamere","Gnar","Gnar"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once you have E Spinning Slash you can commit to a Q Bloodlust-fueled all-in, but Gnar's boomerang Q and Hyper-empowered autos out-poke you at range, so pick your window when his Q is down."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"This is your cleanest fight: mini Gnar has no reliable escape and can't reach Mega form on demand, so if you land E in and pop R Undying Rage he simply can't burst through your immortality."},{"when":"1st item","text":"The moment Gnar hits Mega form he flips the lane — GNAR! stun into E-W knockback plus Botrk/Steraks armor lets him body you even through R, so respect his rage bar."},{"when":"Late","text":"Mega Gnar in a teamfight walls you off and CCs you out of the carry — you must split away from his rage windows and only dive when his transform is on cooldown."}],"wants":{"you":["Fight while he is stuck in mini form with no CC","Catch him with E when his boomerang Q is on cooldown","All-in at 6 before he can reach Mega reliably"],"foe":["Poke you down with boomerang Q and Hyper autos from range","Transform to Mega and land GNAR! stun into E knockback","Kite you with Mega W-E displacement while items online"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are an even farm phase — Gnar's boomerang Q and ranged autos out-trade you, but neither of you has kill pressure, so soak minions and dodge his returning Q rather than forcing bad short trades.","mid":"From level 3 you gain E all-in threat, and level 6 is your spike: against mini Gnar with no escape, E-in plus R Undying Rage lets you win any straight duel, so bait him low and commit while his rage bar is not full.","late":"Once Gnar reaches Mega form and picks up Botrk/Steraks the matchup inverts — his GNAR! stun and E-W knockback can peel you off even through your ult, so play the sidelane around his transform cooldown and avoid his rage windows.","whys":["Level 1 is an even lane-opener where neither of you commits so it reads as a skill farm.","Level 2 stays skill-based as Gnar pokes with Q but has no all-in to punish you.","Level 3 is roughly even — you gain E threat but his ranged poke offsets it.","At levels 4-5 Gnar's stacked boomerang and Hyper autos out-poke you before your spike, favoring him.","At level 6 mini Gnar has no escape, so your E plus R Undying Rage all-in favors you.","At first item Mega form's GNAR! stun and knockback plus Botrk let Gnar body you.","With two-plus items Mega Gnar's CC and durability wall you off the fight, favoring him."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"gragas","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"With E Spinning Slash you can gap-close onto Gragas the instant his Body Slam E is down — that dash is his only escape and disengage, so bait it or wait it out, then Q-fueled all-in while he has no bump."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R Undying Rage beats his kill pattern cleanly: even if he lands Explosive Cask R to knock you around, you pop your immortality, keep autoing, and heal back up with Q before he can reset his cooldowns."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You out-scale his damage hard once you have crit — Gragas is a tanky mage with no reliable single-target kill on you, so a Botrk/IE spike lets you shred him through his passive shielding."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game he becomes a utility CC-bot; your job is to E onto his carries and use R to survive his Cask, since he can't 1v1 you but can peel with W damage reduction and knockups."}],"wants":{"you":["E onto him the moment Body Slam E is on cooldown","All-in with Q sustain while he lacks his escape","Pop R through his Explosive Cask and keep autoing"],"foe":["Poke you with barrel Q and shove to deny short trades","Use Body Slam E to disengage every time you commit","Land Explosive Cask R to knock you away from him"]},"early":"Level 1 you already have the edge — Gragas has to walk up to last-hit into your auto range, and his barrel Q costs a lot of mana early, so deny his CS and threaten him whenever his E is down.","mid":"Levels 2-3 are a skill phase over positioning and his Body Slam cooldown, but from level 4 onward your E all-in plus Q Bloodlust sustain lets you win extended trades any time his bump is unavailable.","late":"With crit items online you dominate the 1v1 — R Undying Rage neutralizes his Explosive Cask burst, so E onto him or his backline, tank the knock with your ult, and heal through his kit while your autos delete him.","whys":["Level 1 favors you since Gragas must expose himself to CS and his Q is mana-costly.","Level 2 is a skill window decided by his Body Slam positioning before your all-in comes online.","Level 3 stays even as you gain E but he still has his escape up to disengage.","At levels 4-5 your E plus Q sustain all-in beats him whenever his bump is down, favoring you.","At level 6 R Undying Rage nullifies his Cask kill pattern, so the spike is yours.","At first item your crit spike shreds the tanky mage who can't 1v1 you.","With two-plus items you still out-duel him hard since he has no single-target kill on you."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"graves","win":["Skill","Graves","Skill","Tryndamere","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Graves' level-2 spike with Q Buckshot and E dash burst hurts, but once you have E Spinning Slash at 3+ you can dodge his Smoke Screen W blind and gap-close — commit only when his E dash charges are spent so he can't reposition out."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Roughly even here — R Undying Rage lets you survive his combo burst, but Graves' raw AA-reload damage and True Grit resists mean if you mistime the ult he can still kill you before it comes up."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your crit spike starts to overtake his lane-bully phase; if you E in past his Smoke Screen and stick with Q sustain, his lack of sustained single-target DPS lets you grind him down."},{"when":"Late","text":"You out-duel Graves late — his damage is front-loaded and burst-shaped, so R eats his combo and your continuous crit autos plus Q healing win any extended fight once his E dashes are used."}],"wants":{"you":["Wait out his E dash charges before you all-in","Dodge Smoke Screen W so you aren't blinded mid-trade","Use R to survive his burst then grind with crit autos"],"foe":["Blow you up at level 2 with Q Buckshot plus E burst","Blind you with Smoke Screen W to negate your autos","Kite with E dashes and reload autos through True Grit"]},"early":"Level 1 is an even opener, but level 2 is Graves' window — his Q Buckshot plus E dash burst and the Smoke Screen blind let him win the short trade hard, so give ground and don't contest until you have E.","mid":"Levels 3-5 swing on execution: your E all-in comes online and lets you close past his Smoke Screen, but his front-loaded damage keeps level 6 a coin-flip decided by whether you time R Undying Rage correctly.","late":"From first item onward the matchup tilts to you — Graves is a burst duelist with no sustained single-target DPS, so R absorbs his combo and your continuous crit autos plus Q Bloodlust healing overwhelm him once his E charges are spent.","whys":["Level 1 is an even farm opener before Graves reaches his power spike.","Level 2 belongs to Graves — Buckshot plus E burst and the W blind win the trade.","Level 3 evens out as your E all-in threat starts matching his lane-bully damage.","At levels 4-5 your E gap-close past Smoke Screen lets you commit favorably.","At level 6 his front-loaded burst versus your R makes it a skill coin-flip.","At first item your crit spike overtakes his burst-shaped kit, favoring you.","With two-plus items your sustained autos and Q healing out-duel his front-loaded damage."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"gwen","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"With E Spinning Slash you can dash in past her W Hallowed Mist, but note the fog makes her untargetable by autos while she stands in it — force the trade as she steps out to CS, since her Q snips out-poke you if you sit in range."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R Undying Rage is your trump card: Gwen's kill relies on Q Snip Snip! shred plus R Needlework poke, but you pop immortality, ride out her burst, and heal back with Q Bloodlust before her Mist is up again."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You spike harder on crit than she does on her AP scaling early — if you catch her outside Mist with E and stick, her fragile early durability means you shred her before she can re-fog."},{"when":"Late","text":"Gwen out-scales most bruisers, but you specifically counter her: R negates her Needlework execute and your continuous crit sustain wins the extended fight as long as you don't waste E into her Mist."}],"wants":{"you":["Force trades when she steps out of Hallowed Mist","E in and all-in while her W fog is on cooldown","Use R to survive her Q shred then heal with Bloodlust"],"foe":["Sit in Hallowed Mist W to dodge your autos and E","Poke you with Q snips and R Needlework from range","Scale her AP and stack Snip Snip! shred on you"]},"early":"Level 1 favors you — Gwen is melee-range and mana-light but has no CC or escape until her W, so walk her down and deny CS while she has nothing to zone you with.","mid":"Levels 2-3 are a skill phase around her Hallowed Mist timing and Q poke, but from level 4 your E all-in plus Q sustain lets you win any trade you start while her fog is down.","late":"Even into her scaling, you hold the edge — R Undying Rage eats her Q shred and R Needlework burst, and your crit autos plus Bloodlust healing grind her down whenever you can pull her off her Mist.","whys":["Level 1 favors you since Gwen has no CC or escape to stop you walking her down.","Level 2 is skill-based around her first W Mist and Q poke timing.","Level 3 stays even as her Mist zoning offsets your emerging E threat.","At levels 4-5 your E all-in beats her whenever Hallowed Mist is on cooldown, favoring you.","At level 6 R Undying Rage negates her Q-plus-R burst, so the spike is yours.","At first item your crit outpaces her early AP scaling and shreds her out of Mist.","With two-plus items your R and sustained autos still counter her scaling and win extended fights."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"heimerdinger","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Heimerdinger","Tryndamere","Heimerdinger","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"His H-28G turrets zone you off the wave and chunk you as you walk up, and E Spinning Slash into a turret nest just eats grenade stuns — hold your dash and clear turrets with autos before you ever try to touch Heimer."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Level 6 is your window: R Undying Rage lets you dive through his turret damage and the R-upgraded grenade, tank the CC, and kill him — he has no escape, so if you save E to close after his W poke you win the all-in."},{"when":"1st item","text":"He spikes back at first item — an upgraded turret from his R plus rylai/liandry poke re-establishes the zone, and if you E in without clearing turrets first his E grenade stun locks you for the burst."},{"when":"Late","text":"Split-push away from his lane and only engage with R up — a full turret nest plus grenade stun can chain you long enough to kill even through your ult if you dive carelessly, so pick your dive when his CE grenade is down."}],"wants":{"you":["Save E to close only after his W grenade is used","Dive at 6 with R up through the turret damage","Clear turrets with autos before committing to Heimer"],"foe":["Zone you off farm with the H-28G turret nest","Land E grenade stun to lock you for turret burst","Re-establish the zone with R-upgraded turret and poke"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are a farming struggle decided by skill — Heimer's turrets zone you off CS and poke you as you walk up, so soak what you can safely, avoid his Q grenade, and don't waste E trying to reach him through the nest.","mid":"Level 4-5 leans to Heimer as his stacked turrets and W poke chip you before you spike, but level 6 flips it: R Undying Rage lets you dive through the nest, tank the grenade stun, and kill him since he has no escape.","late":"He reasserts control at first item with an R-upgraded turret and poke items, so play the sidelane and only dive when his CE grenade stun is on cooldown — with R up and turrets cleared first you still kill him at two-plus items.","whys":["Level 1 is a skill farm phase before his turret zone comes fully online.","Level 2 stays skill-based as you dodge poke and soak CS around his turrets.","Level 3 remains even while you clear turrets and avoid his grenade.","At levels 4-5 his stacked turret nest and W poke zone you out, favoring Heimer.","At level 6 R Undying Rage lets you dive through the turrets and kill him, favoring you.","At first item his R-upgraded turret and poke items re-establish the zone, favoring Heimer.","With two-plus items you can dive him when his grenade is down and R is up, favoring you."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"illaoi","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Illaoi"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Never stand near her tentacles or in a spawned Test of Spirit vessel — her E rips your spirit and the tentacle slams shred you fast. Use E Spinning Slash to dodge her Q tentacle smash, not to engage, and only trade when tentacles are on cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"This is your key window: her R Leap of Faith spawns a ring of tentacles for a huge AoE, but R Undying Rage lets you pop immortality, ride out the tentacle storm, and Q-heal through it — bait her ult, survive, then kill her as the tentacles expire."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With crit you can burst her between tentacle slams, but you must respect Test of Spirit — if she pulls your spirit, walk away from the tentacles entirely rather than fighting her at full tentacle count."},{"when":"Late","text":"Illaoi out-scales you in a committed brawl — a full late-game tentacle field with R plus Titanic/Steraks can out-damage even your R heal window, so avoid fighting in her tentacles and only engage when her E and R are down."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait her R Leap of Faith then survive it with your R","Fight only when her tentacles are on cooldown","Use E to dodge her Q smash, not to engage"],"foe":["Land Test of Spirit E to shred your spirit vessel","Fight you inside a full field of tentacle slams","Scale late with R plus tank items to out-brawl you"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are a careful skill phase — Illaoi has no early kill pressure without landing E, so soak CS at max range, dodge her telegraphed Q tentacle smash, and never fight beside her tentacles where the slams stack up.","mid":"Level 5-6 is your spike: R Undying Rage is the perfect answer to her R Leap of Faith, letting you tank the whole tentacle storm and heal through with Q while she blows her biggest cooldown for nothing.","late":"With crit you can duel her when her tentacles are down, but late game she out-scales you — a full tentacle field plus tank items out-damages your R window, so avoid the committed brawl and only engage after she uses E and R.","whys":["Levels 1-2 are an even farm phase since Illaoi has no kill threat without landing E.","Level 2 stays skill-based as you soak CS and dodge her Q smash.","Level 3 remains even while you avoid fighting near her tentacles.","At level 4 it is still skill-decided around her tentacle spacing and E.","At level 5 R Undying Rage lets you survive her R storm and kill her, favoring you.","At first item your crit lets you burst her between slams when tentacles are down, favoring you.","With two-plus items her full tentacle field plus tank items out-scale and out-brawl you."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"irelia","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Irelia","Irelia","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Irelia's level 3-4 is her power window — once she has Q Bladesurge resets off minions and W Defiant Dance parry, she can dash through the wave onto you and block your key auto. Don't fight into a full wave, and hold E Spinning Slash to disengage rather than to commit."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Even here, but you tilt it — R Undying Rage lets you survive her E Flawless Duet stun combo and R Vanguard's Edge burst, then Q-heal back. If she blows her combo and you ult through it, you win the reset."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your crit spike catches up to her tempo — she stacks passive off short trades, so avoid feeding her resets and instead all-in when her Q dash charges and W parry are down, where your sustained autos out-damage her."},{"when":"Late","text":"You out-scale Irelia into the late game — R eats her burst combo and your continuous crit autos plus Q sustain grind her down, as long as you fight in open space where she can't chain Bladesurge resets off minions."}],"wants":{"you":["All-in when her W parry and Q dash charges are down","Fight in open space with no minions for her to reset on","Use R to survive her E stun combo then heal with Q"],"foe":["Reset Q Bladesurge off the wave to dash onto you","Parry your key auto with W Defiant Dance","Land E Flawless Duet stun into R burst combo"]},"early":"Level 1 favors you — Irelia is weak before her Q resets come online, so walk up and deny her CS while she has no dash charges to threaten you or escape.","mid":"Levels 3-4 are Irelia's spike: with Q resets and W parry she dashes through minions onto you and blocks your autos, so don't fight into a full wave — level 5-6 evens out as R Undying Rage lets you survive her stun combo.","late":"From first item onward you take over — your crit sustain out-damages her short-trade tempo, R negates her E-R burst, and continuous autos plus Q healing win the extended fight as long as you deny her minion resets.","whys":["Level 1 favors you since Irelia is weak before her Q Bladesurge resets are available.","Level 2 is skill-based as she gains W parry but lacks full reset tempo.","At level 3 Irelia's Q resets and dash tempo let her win trades, favoring her.","At level 4 her stacked passive and W parry keep the edge with her.","At level 5 R Undying Rage evens the fight by surviving her stun combo.","At first item your crit sustain overtakes her short-trade tempo, favoring you.","With two-plus items your R and continuous autos plus Q healing out-scale her burst."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"jax","win":["Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Skill","Skill","Skill","Jax","Jax"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Jax has E Counter Strike but no dash charges yet if he skills Leap Strike late, so you can trade with Q Bloodlust auto weaving as long as you sidestep the Counter Strike stun window; the trade goes even once he has both W and E up."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Jax R Grandmaster's Might swings the duel hard: the passive third-hit magic proc plus the armor/MR bonus means your raw crit output no longer out-DPSes him, so respect all-ins the moment his ult is available."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Jax scaling into Blade of the Ruined King or Divine Sunderer with Counter Strike stun makes an even fight a losing one for you; Undying Rage lets you survive one Counter Strike but he simply re-engages once your R ends."},{"when":"Late","text":"Full-build Jax with E stun uptime and R resistances beats you in an extended duel; use your superior split-push mobility with E Spinning Slash resets rather than face-checking him in a bruiser slugfest."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait or dodge Counter Strike before you commit any Q-empowered trade","Snowball levels 1-2 before his ult and stun scaling take over","Use E Spinning Slash mobility to split and avoid even bruiser duels"],"foe":["Land Counter Strike stun to eat your crit burst and turn the trade","Reach level 6 R for the resist bonus and third-hit magic proc","Build BorK/Sunderer and drag you into a sustained duel"]},"early":"You own levels 1-2: Jax is a weak early laner with no dash charges and a clunky Counter Strike, so auto-Q-auto trades with your Battle Fury crit chance favour you before he has both spells online.","mid":"Levels 3-6 flatten to skill: Jax gains Leap Strike and Counter Strike, and the fight hinges entirely on whether you dodge his stun window or eat it, with neither side clearly ahead until his ult lands.","late":"From level 6 and items onward Jax overtakes you: Grandmaster's Might resistances and stun uptime beat raw crit in a straight duel, so pivot to split-pushing and picking flanks rather than dueling him head-on.","whys":["You dominate level 1 as a strong early duelist against a famously weak-early Jax with no dash charges.","You stay ahead at level 2 while Jax still lacks both W and E to trade back safely.","At level 3 it evens out once Jax has Leap Strike and Counter Strike to answer your trades.","Levels 4-5 stay even as the fight comes down to dodging his stun versus landing your crits.","Level 6 tips to Jax: Grandmaster's Might adds resists and a magic proc that out-duels your crit.","At first item Jax's BorK/Sunderer plus stun uptime beats you in a sustained fight.","Late game Jax's scaling resistances and reliable stun make the extended duel his."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"jayce","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Jayce","Tryndamere","Jayce","Jayce"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Jayce pokes with Ranged Q Shock Blast into Acceleration Gate and can knock you back with Melee W Thundering Blow, so you must use minions to block the long-range Q and only commit when his Gate is down; early trades are a skill test of dodging his poke line."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"You get no dramatic level-6 spike since Undying Rage is already available, but this is your window: Jayce has no real ultimate, so once you close distance with E Spinning Slash and pop R you can force a fight he can't disengage from with a single knockback."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Jayce's early-item poke damage (Manamune/Eclipse) lets him zone you off the wave and chunk you before you ever engage; if you fall behind on HP his Shock Blast burst can nearly kill you before Undying Rage even matters."},{"when":"Late","text":"Jayce scales his poke and burst better into the mid game and can whittle you before any all-in; his mobility with Acceleration Gate and Ranged E To The Skies lets him kite your Spinning Slash and win the extended lane."}],"wants":{"you":["Body-block Ranged Q Shock Blast with minions and dodge his poke line","Force the all-in at level 6 when his Gate/W are on cooldown","Sustain his poke off with Q Bloodlust heals and freeze near tower"],"foe":["Poke you down with Shock Blast + Acceleration Gate before you engage","Knock you away with Thundering Blow to reset every trade","Kite your Spinning Slash with To The Skies and ranged form range"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are a skill matchup: Jayce wants to poke with Ranged Q Shock Blast and you want to block it with minions and heal off the chip with Q Bloodlust, so the lane state depends on how cleanly each of you dodges.","mid":"At level 4 Jayce edges ahead with his poke online, but level 6 is your spike window: Jayce has no true ultimate, so if you E in and Undying Rage through his burst you can win a committed all-in he can't cleanly disengage.","late":"Past first item Jayce takes over again: his Shock Blast burst and Acceleration Gate mobility let him poke you low and kite your Spinning Slash, so all-in early or you lose the extended poke war.","whys":["Level 1 is even; Jayce's poke isn't online and you can't yet close the gap.","Level 2 stays a skill test of dodging Shock Blast versus healing it off.","Level 3 remains even as both of you jockey over his poke line and your engage timing.","At level 4 Jayce pulls ahead once his Shock Blast + Gate poke is fully online.","Level 6 favours you: Jayce lacks a real ultimate, so your R all-in overwhelms his single knockback disengage.","At first item Jayce's Manamune/Eclipse poke chunks you before you can engage.","Late game Jayce's burst and Acceleration Gate kiting win the extended lane."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"karma","win":["Skill","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Karma's Q Inner Flame and empowered RQ Soulflare poke you from range, but she is squishy with no hard escape beyond E Inspire's shield/speed; once you hit level 3 with E Spinning Slash you can jump her and Q Bloodlust auto her down before her shield outlasts your crits."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Karma gets no ultimate power spike (her R just upgrades an ability) so your level-6 Undying Rage lets you dive her freely; she can Mantra-E shield and W Focused Resolve root you, but if you save E to dodge the W tether you kill her through the shield."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You spike harder than Karma at first item: your crit-plus-lifesteal build shreds her low base defenses, and as long as you cleanse or outrange the W Focused Resolve root with Spinning Slash mobility, she has no way to survive your all-in."},{"when":"Late","text":"Karma provides team utility but one-on-one she can't beat your sustained crit damage; sidelane her and she folds, though respect her W root plus Mantra shield combo which can buy just enough time for her jungler to arrive."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 3 E to close on her squishy frame and all-in","Dodge or outrange W Focused Resolve root before you commit","Use Q Bloodlust lifesteal to out-sustain her Inner Flame poke"],"foe":["Poke you down early with Q Inner Flame and RQ Soulflare","Root you with W Focused Resolve to kite and peel","Shield with Mantra-E to survive your burst until help arrives"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are even as Karma pokes with Q Inner Flame and you sustain the chip off with Q Bloodlust; she's squishy but you can't yet reliably close the gap without your dash.","mid":"From level 3 you take over: E Spinning Slash lets you jump her fragile frame and crit her down faster than her E shield lasts, and level 6 changes nothing for her since Karma's R only empowers a spell rather than adding an escape.","late":"Post-first-item you stay ahead: your crit and lifesteal shred her low defenses, and as long as you respect the W Focused Resolve root you win every sidelane duel despite her team utility.","whys":["Level 1 is even as Karma's ranged poke trades with your Q sustain before you have a gap-closer.","Level 2 stays a skill test with neither champ able to commit decisively.","At level 3 you pull ahead once E Spinning Slash lets you close on her squishy frame.","Levels 4-5 stay yours as you crit through her E shield faster than it regenerates.","Level 6 evens on paper since her R gives no escape, but the lane is already yours; marked skill for her Mantra timing.","At first item your crit-lifesteal build shreds her low defenses for a favoured all-in.","Late game your sustained duel damage beats her utility kit one-on-one."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"kassadin","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Kassadin's Q Null Sphere shields him from your magic-free crits' spell interrupt and his W Nether Blade sustains his mana, but he has no mobility pre-6 and his early damage is weak; you should be all-inning him repeatedly with E Spinning Slash and Q Bloodlust autos to deny his scaling before Riftwalk exists."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your level-6 window is critical: Kassadin gets R Riftwalk to blink away, but the very first cast is cheap and short-ranged, so if you E in and Undying Rage you can often kill him before he stacks enough Riftwalks to escape; this is your last easy kill before he spikes."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You favour first item because Kassadin is still a wet-noodle mid-game melee-range caster before his AP items come online; keep the wave shoved, deny his farm, and punish every step forward while your crit build out-damages his early kit."},{"when":"Late","text":"This is the danger zone reflected in the low win rate: fully-stacked Riftwalk lets Kassadin blink around your Spinning Slash and one-combo squishies, and his Q shield plus Rod of Ages bulk make him nearly unkillable, so you must end the game before he completes two items."}],"wants":{"you":["All-in relentlessly levels 1-5 while Kassadin has no escape","Kill him at level 6 before Riftwalk stacks refund the cost","Shove waves to deny farm and starve his AP scaling"],"foe":["Survive the early lane and farm safely under tower","Reach stacked Riftwalk to blink away from your Spinning Slash","Complete Rod of Ages/AP items to out-scale and one-combo you"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 read as skill but you must play them aggressively: Kassadin has no mobility and feeble early damage, so E-in trades with Q Bloodlust autos let you chunk him, and only his Q Null Sphere shield gives him any safety.","mid":"Level 5-6 is your make-or-break window and it favours you: before Riftwalk stacks up, an E plus Undying Rage all-in kills him outright, and first item still finds him a squishy, immobile caster you out-crit.","late":"The extended game is his and it's why the win rate sinks: stacked Riftwalk kites your Spinning Slash and his AP burst plus Q shield make him slippery and lethal, so close the game out before his second item lands.","whys":["Level 1 is even on paper but you should press the immobile Kassadin; marked skill for his Q shield safety.","Level 2 stays a skill lane as neither champ commits fully yet.","Level 3 remains even though your E trades chunk his weak early kit.","Levels 4-5 stay skill as he farms safely and you look for all-in openings.","Level 6 favours you: first-cast Riftwalk is cheap and short, so your R all-in can kill before he escapes.","At first item you're ahead while he's still a squishy immobile caster pre-AP.","Late game flips hard to Kassadin: stacked Riftwalk and AP burst out-scale your crit."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"kayle","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Kayle is melee and helpless until level 6, but her E Starfire Spellblade and Q Radiant Blast slow give her some poke; you should be walking her down with E Spinning Slash and Q Bloodlust autos every wave, since she has zero kill pressure and only wants to survive to her ranged form."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your level-6 spike is the whole game: Kayle's R Divine Judgment gives her a few seconds of invulnerability, but if you E in, chunk her, and Undying Rage through her ult's damage window, she has no escape to actually get away once her R immunity ends."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You strongly favour first item: Kayle hits ranged form at level 6 but is still weak and item-starved, so keep the wave shoving into her tower, deny CS, and all-in whenever your jungler pressures, choking her out before she reaches level 11 and 16 spikes."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game is Kayle's if she survives, but that's beyond lane; your job is to make her miserable early so she never scales, since a farmed ranged Kayle with Nashor's/Guinsoo out-damages you from a range your Spinning Slash can't consistently close."}],"wants":{"you":["Walk her down every wave while she's melee and weak pre-6","Shove and deny CS to starve her scaling","All-in through R Divine Judgment's invuln window then kill her after"],"foe":["Survive lane and farm to hit ranged form and level 11/16 spikes","Use R Divine Judgment invulnerability to blank your all-in","Poke with E Starfire once ranged to chip you safely"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 read as skill but heavily pressure them: Kayle is melee, poke-only, and has no kill threat, so E-in trades with Q Bloodlust autos let you bully her while she just tries to farm to level 6.","mid":"Level 5-6 tips to you: even after she hits ranged form, she's fragile and item-starved, and your E-plus-Undying-Rage all-in kills her once her R Divine Judgment invulnerability expires since she has no true escape.","late":"First item stays yours as you keep her choked under tower, but understand the clock — a fully scaled Kayle out-ranges and out-damages you, so you must snowball the lane and end before her level 11 and 16 spikes.","whys":["Level 1 is even on paper but you should bully the melee Kayle; skill marked for her survival play.","Level 2 stays skill as she pokes and farms without kill pressure.","Level 3 remains even while you look to walk her down with E trades.","Levels 4-5 stay skill as she scrapes toward her level-6 ranged form.","Level 6 favours you: you all-in through Divine Judgment and kill her after the invuln ends.","At first item you're ahead while she's still fragile and item-starved.","Late game you stay favoured in lane provided you've denied her the farm to scale."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"kennen","win":["Kennen","Skill","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Kennen's Q Thundering Shuriken and W Electrical Surge poke you from range and stack Mark of the Storm, but he's squishy and immobile without E Lightning Rush charged; once you reach level 4 you can E Spinning Slash onto him and Q Bloodlust auto him down before he can stun you with a third mark."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"You favour level 6: Kennen R Slicing Maelstrom is a teamfight tool, and one-on-one your Undying Rage lets you all-in through his stun-and-ult combo and survive the damage while your crits shred his low HP frame before the maelstrom finishes ticking."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You spike hard at first item: your crit-lifesteal build out-damages Kennen's fragile body, and as long as you don't eat a full three-mark stun into his ult with no R up, you win every all-in; save Undying Rage for his stun window."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late one-on-one you beat Kennen since he's squishy and your sustained crits melt him, but respect his ability to E-in, stun-lock, and ult you in a coordinated collapse; sidelane pressure with Spinning Slash is your win condition."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge early Q Thundering Shuriken poke and avoid the third Mark stun","All-in from level 4 once E can close on his squishy frame","Save Undying Rage for his stun-into-R combo then crit him down"],"foe":["Poke you down and land a three-mark stun before you engage","Use E Lightning Rush to disengage and re-poke","Chain stun into R Slicing Maelstrom during a jungle gank"]},"early":"Level 1 favours Kennen: his ranged Q Thundering Shuriken poke chunks you before you have E to close, and eating an early Mark of the Storm stun can snowball against you. Levels 2-3 even out as you weather the poke with Q Bloodlust sustain.","mid":"From level 4 you take over: E Spinning Slash closes onto his fragile frame and your crits shred him faster than his poke replenishes, and level 6 stays yours since Undying Rage lets you all-in straight through his stun-and-ult combo.","late":"First item and beyond stay favoured: your crit-lifesteal build melts his squishy body one-on-one, so keep the sidelane pressure on with Spinning Slash while only respecting his full stun-into-Maelstrom combo when his jungler is near.","whys":["Level 1 goes to Kennen: his ranged shuriken poke and Mark stun punish you before you have a gap-closer.","Level 2 evens out as you sustain his poke with Q Bloodlust.","Level 3 stays skill while you weather marks and wait for your E spike.","At level 4 you pull ahead once E Spinning Slash closes onto his squishy frame.","Level 6 stays yours: Undying Rage lets you all-in through his stun-and-ult combo.","At first item your crit-lifesteal build out-damages his fragile body.","Late game your sustained crits melt him one-on-one in the sidelane."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"kled","win":["Kled","Kled","Kled","Kled","Kled","Skill","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Kled dominates early: his Q Bear Trap on a Rope pulls and slows you, W Violent Tendencies gives him a burst of empowered autos, and mounted on Skaarl he simply out-trades your crits with more effective HP; avoid extended fights and give up CS rather than eat a Q pull into his W burst."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Kled stays ahead at level 6: his R Chaaaaaaaarge!!! is roam and engage pressure, and in lane he out-sustains and out-trades you while mounted, so respect his all-in and use Undying Rage purely to survive rather than to win the duel."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Kled remains favoured at first item since his empowered W autos plus dismount-remount mechanic give him staying power your crits struggle to burst through; only when you get him off Skaarl and he's in unmounted low-HP form do trades swing your way."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game finally tips to you: your scaling crit and lifesteal out-duel Kled once fights go long and your items come online, and if you can force him off his mount his weak dismounted stats let you finish him; split-push with Spinning Slash and duel him only when he's unhorsed."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive the brutal early lane by giving up CS over eating Q pulls","Dismount him off Skaarl to exploit his weak unmounted form","Scale to your crit-lifesteal item spike then duel long fights"],"foe":["Land Q Bear Trap pull into W Violent Tendencies burst","Out-trade you while mounted with his extra effective HP","Snowball the early levels before your scaling comes online"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are firmly Kled's: his Q Bear Trap pull, W Violent Tendencies burst, and mounted effective HP let him win every early trade, so play safe, dodge the Q, and concede CS rather than feed his lead.","mid":"Levels 4-6 stay Kled's — mounted on Skaarl he out-sustains and out-trades your crits, and even Undying Rage only buys you survival, not a won duel; wait for him to overextend or get dismounted rather than forcing fights.","late":"First item is still his but late game finally flips to you: once your crit-lifesteal build is online you out-duel him in extended fights, and forcing him off his mount exposes his flimsy unmounted stats for the kill.","whys":["Level 1 goes to Kled: Q pull into W burst and mounted HP win the trade outright.","Level 2 stays Kled's as his empowered autos out-damage your early crits.","Level 3 remains his while Skaarl's effective HP shrugs off your trades.","Levels 4-5 stay Kled's as he out-sustains and out-trades you mounted.","Level 6 is still his: R adds pressure and Undying Rage only helps you survive, not win.","At first item Kled's remount staying power out-lasts your crit burst.","Late game finally tips to you once your crit-lifesteal scaling out-duels him."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"ksante","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Skill","K'Sante","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"K'Sante's level 3 all-in with W charge into Q knock-up and Ntofo Strikes stacking is his cleanest window; respect the W stun and don't sit in his Q line while he has passive stacks up."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"You hit 6 and R Undying Rage flips the lane: bait his All Out (R) transformation, tank the burst through your ghost window, and Q back to full while he's out of dashes."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With a crit shard and Q sustain you out-DPS his tank stats; his passive true-damage on marks is his only real threat, so kite his Ntofo stacks and E away from the reset."},{"when":"Late","text":"Split-push freely; K'Sante is a teamfight tank, not a duelist, and your R plus lifesteal means he can never solo-kill you in a sidelane."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 6 with R up","Kite his Ntofo Strike (Q) stacks","Free split-push after items"],"foe":["Land the W charge stun into Q knock-up","Stack passive marks for true damage","Group for teamfights with All Out (R)"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 favour you: K'Sante is weak before his Ntofo Strike (Q) stacking comes online, so trade with Q Bloodlust auto-resets and shove the wave. Don't stand in his Q cast line and you take almost no free damage early.","mid":"Levels 3-6 tighten to a skill window — his level 3 W-charge stun into Q knock-up is a real all-in, and misplaying into his passive marks costs you true damage. Play the wave, dodge the W, and hold Spinning Slash (E) as a defensive escape until your ult arrives.","late":"Once you have R and a first-item crit spike you overwhelm his tank stats: bait All Out (R), survive on your ghost window, and Q Bloodlust back to full. Take the sidelane and pressure — he cannot answer your split.","whys":["You out-trade a stackless K'Sante at level 1-2 before his Q passive comes online.","Level 2 is even — his kit is still forming and your Q reset trade is matched by his poke.","Level 3 is a coin-flip: his W-charge stun all-in versus your ability to dodge and punish it.","Levels 4-5 favour K'Sante — full Ntofo stacks and passive true damage let him win extended trades before your ult.","Level 6 flips to you: R Undying Rage negates his All Out burst and lets you Q back to full.","With a crit item your sustained DPS and lifesteal outscale his tank stats in a duel.","At two-plus items you split-push freely because a teamfight tank can never solo-kill you."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"lillia","win":["Skill","Tryndamere","Skill","Tryndamere","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Lillia wants to kite with Blooming Blows (Q) and Watch Out! (W) poke; close the gap with Spinning Slash (E) the instant her W is down and she has nothing to peel you off."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her R Lullaby sleep is a pick threat but slow-travelling — you hit 6 too and R Undying Rage lets you tank the sleep-empowered burst and Q back up."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With lifesteal online her magic DoT poke can't out-race your Q sustain; run her down whenever her E dash is on cooldown."},{"when":"Late","text":"You hard-outscale her in a sidelane — she's a teamfight AP skirmisher with no lock-down for a diver on top of her, so split and force her off the map."}],"wants":{"you":["Gap-close with E when her W is down","Sustain through her DoT with Q lifesteal","Split-push and dodge her R Lullaby"],"foe":["Kite with Blooming Blows (Q) movement speed","Poke safely with Watch Out! (W)","Land R Lullaby for a sleep pick"]},"early":"Level 1 is a skill window — Lillia's Blooming Blows (Q) gives her movement speed to kite and you have to respect her early poke. Farm safely and don't over-extend into a gank-friendly wave.","mid":"You take control through the mid-levels: once you have Spinning Slash (E) you can force the gap the moment her Watch Out! (W) is on cooldown, and her squishy AP body folds to Q Bloodlust auto-resets. Levels 3 and 5 are even because a whiffed E or a good W-Q combo from her swings the trade, but level 4 clearly favours you.","late":"With a crit and lifesteal item you overwhelm her — her magic DoT can't out-sustain your Q, and R Undying Rage nullifies any Lullaby-setup burst. Take the sidelane; she has no way to hold a diver off her.","whys":["Level 1 is even — her Q kiting movement speed offsets your melee-range trade attempts.","Level 2 favours you as your Q reset trade beats her weak early damage before her poke ramps.","Level 3 is a skill coin-flip on whether she lands W-Q poke or you land your gap-close.","Level 4 favours you — with E online you dictate the gap and punish her squishy body.","Level 5 is even because her R and full poke kit give her a pick option if you misstep.","With lifesteal your Q sustain out-races her DoT poke and you run her down.","Late you hard-outscale a teamfight AP skirmisher who can't peel a diver in a sidelane."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"lucian","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Lucian","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Lucian's Piercing Light (Q) and Relentless Pursuit (E) dash let him poke-and-reset your Q Bloodlust stacks; walk up behind minions to deny his Q line and don't let him free-poke."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His R Culling shreds you in the open, but you have your own R — pop Undying Rage before The Culling finishes and Q Bloodlust back to full while he's channeled out."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once you land your first crit item you flip the lane: Spinning Slash (E) onto him the moment his E dash is down and he has no escape from your run-down."},{"when":"Late","text":"You hard-outscale a lane-bully marksman — Lucian falls off in extended duels and your R plus lifesteal make you unkillable in a sidelane 1v1."}],"wants":{"you":["Block his Q with minions","Bait or wait out his E dash before engaging","Reach items and R to flip the run-down"],"foe":["Free-poke with Piercing Light (Q)","Reset spacing with Relentless Pursuit (E)","Burst you inside R Culling"]},"early":"Early levels are a skill matchup — Lucian's double-tap passive and Piercing Light (Q) let him poke you down, but he's melee-range-punishable if he steps up to CS. Block his Q with minions and farm; don't take unfavourable poke trades before you have sustain.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are Lucian's window: his Q-E-Q rhythm chunks you and his R Culling can shred your health bar before your own ult is a factor. Respect his burst, hold Spinning Slash (E) to disengage rather than to chase, and wait for your item spike.","late":"From your first crit item onward you take over — Lucian is a lane bully who fades in extended fights, so E onto him when his dash is down and run him down. With R Undying Rage and lifesteal you win every sidelane 1v1 and can split freely.","whys":["Level 1 is even — his ranged Q poke is offset by your ability to farm safely behind minions.","Level 2 stays skill-based as neither of you commits a hard all-in yet.","Level 3 is even: his Q-E poke rhythm is matched by your minion-blocking and CS discipline.","Levels 4-5 favour Lucian — his Q-E burst and R Culling out-damage you before your item spike.","Level 6 is even because your R Undying Rage cancels the value of his R Culling burst.","With your first crit item your sustained DPS overtakes his fading lane-bully damage.","Late you hard-outscale a marksman who can't survive your run-down with R and lifesteal up."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"malphite","win":["Skill","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Skill","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is your only real window — before Malphite stacks armor and Sunfire, punish his low base damage: E in, burn Q Bloodlust resets, and shove him under tower repeatedly."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His R Unstoppable Force is a point-and-click knock-up you can't dodge in lane; play at max range, never hug the wall, and hold your E to disengage after he ults."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Malphite's armor stacking plus Thornmail turn your crits against you — Bramble/Frozen Heart gut your DPS and your Q sustain can't out-race his passive shield poke."},{"when":"Late","text":"He's a teamfight engage tank who outscales you into armor items; avoid solo all-ins, prioritise objectives and don't chase him into his R+flash pick range."}],"wants":{"you":["Punish his weak levels 3-5","Shove him under tower with Q resets","Fight before he buys armor"],"foe":["Stack armor and Thornmail vs your crit","Poke free with passive shield up","Land R Unstoppable Force knock-up"]},"early":"Early levels are a skill matchup that quietly favours the tank — Malphite's passive shield lets him poke or absorb your trades, and you can't kill through his armor start. Farm cleanly and look only for chip trades where his shield is down.","mid":"Levels 3-5 are your best and only real window: before his armor and Sunfire come online his base damage is low, so E in, burn Q Bloodlust resets, and shove him under tower. Once he hits 6, his R Unstoppable Force is an undodgeable knock-up — respect it and never hug walls.","late":"Malphite hard-counters your crit build into items — Thornmail and stacked armor turn your autos against you and your Q can't out-sustain his passive poke. Avoid solo all-ins, play for objectives, and don't over-commit to a sidelane where his R-flash picks you.","whys":["Level 1 is even but tilts to Malphite — his passive shield blunts your early trades.","Level 2 stays a skill window as neither champion threatens a kill yet.","Level 3 favours you: his base damage is low and your E-in Q-reset trade wins before armor.","Levels 4-5 stay yours — this is the pre-armor window where you can shove and punish him.","Level 6 is even because his R Unstoppable Force knock-up neutralises your all-in threat.","At first item his armor and Thornmail start turning your crits against you — even at best.","Late his stacked armor and teamfight engage outscale your crit duel, keeping it a skill floor."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"maokai","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Skill","Maokai","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Maokai's Twisted Advance (W) root into Sapling Toss (E) poke is his kill setup; stay out of his saplings in brush and don't get W-rooted next to his jungler."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"You hit 6 and R Undying Rage answers his all-in — bait the W root, tank the follow-up through your ghost window, and Q Bloodlust back to full."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With lifesteal your Q sustain out-heals his sapling poke; run him down whenever his W root is on cooldown since it's his only lock-down."},{"when":"Late","text":"Maokai is a peel/engage support-tank with no dueling profile — split-push and he can never solo-kill you with R plus lifesteal up."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 6 with R up","Fight when his W root is down","Split-push after your first item"],"foe":["Land Twisted Advance (W) root","Zone with Sapling Toss (E) poke","Set up ganks with his root lock-down"]},"early":"Level 1 favours you — Maokai's early damage is low and your Q Bloodlust reset trades beat his before saplings ramp. Shove and deny him free brush control.","mid":"Levels 2-5 are a skill window centred on his Twisted Advance (W) root — if he catches you with W into Sapling Toss (E) poke, especially with jungle nearby, the trade goes badly. Level 4 is his clearest window; respect the root, dodge saplings, and hold Spinning Slash (E) as your out until 6.","late":"From level 6 you take over: R Undying Rage nullifies his all-in and a first-item lifesteal spike lets your Q out-sustain his poke. Run him down when his W is on cooldown and split the sidelane — he's a peel tank with no answer to a fed diver.","whys":["Level 1 favours you — your Q reset trade beats Maokai's weak early damage.","Level 2 is even as his Twisted Advance root comes online and threatens a punish.","Level 3 stays a skill window between his W-E root poke and your trade discipline.","Level 4 favours Maokai — his W root into sapling poke, often with jungle, wins the all-in.","Level 6 flips to you: R Undying Rage negates his root-setup all-in and heals you back up.","With lifesteal your Q sustain out-heals his sapling poke and you run him down.","Late you outscale a peel/engage tank who cannot solo-kill you in a sidelane."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"mel","win":["Skill","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Mel wants to poke with Radiant Volley (Q) and zone you with her Rebuttal (W) reflect; bait the W, then E in on the window where her reflect is down and burn Q resets."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her R Solar Snuffer is a lane-wide burst-and-execute, but you have R Undying Rage — pop it before her ult finishes and Q Bloodlust back to full while she's committed."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With lifesteal your Q out-sustains her magic poke; she's a squishy mage with only her W to peel a diver, so run her down when it's on cooldown."},{"when":"Late","text":"You hard-outscale a control mage in a sidelane — no hard CST lock, your R negates her burst, and lifesteal keeps you topped through her poke."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait her W Rebuttal reflect before committing","Gap-close with E on the reflect-down window","Sustain her poke with Q lifesteal"],"foe":["Poke with Radiant Volley (Q)","Reflect your burst with Rebuttal (W)","Zone and execute with R Solar Snuffer"]},"early":"Early levels are a skill window — Mel pokes with Radiant Volley (Q) and can punish a careless dive by reflecting it with Rebuttal (W). Farm behind minions, don't feed her stacks, and only trade when her W is down.","mid":"You take control levels 3-4: once Spinning Slash (E) is online you pick the window her Rebuttal (W) reflect is down and dive her squishy body with Q Bloodlust resets. Level 5 is even because her full poke kit and W can punish a mistimed all-in, so bait the reflect first.","late":"With R Undying Rage and a lifesteal item you overwhelm her — her burst and R Solar Snuffer can't kill through your ult, and your Q out-sustains her magic poke. Split the sidelane; a control mage has no answer to a fed diver on her.","whys":["Level 1 is even — her ranged Q poke trades against your safe minion-blocked farming.","Level 2 stays skill-based as neither champion has a committing all-in yet.","Level 3 favours you: with E online you dictate the gap when her W reflect is down.","Level 4 stays yours — your Q-reset dive shreds her squishy body inside the reflect window.","Level 5 is even because her R and full poke kit give her a punish on a mistimed dive.","With lifesteal your Q sustain out-races her poke and you run her down.","Late you hard-outscale a control mage who can't peel a diver with only her W reflect."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"mordekaiser","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Skill","Mordekaiser","Mordekaiser","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Mordekaiser wants his Q Obliterate into E Death's Grasp pull combo with passive Indestructible shield up; sidestep his Q's fat hit and don't stand still for the E pull."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His R Realm of Death is the danger — inside his death realm your lifesteal and escape are useless, and R Undying Rage's ghost window can be timed out. Never fight him at low health at 6."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Post-first-item you swing it back: bait his R, survive the realm on Undying Rage, and out-sustain his DoT with Q Bloodlust once you're out and he's on cooldown."},{"when":"Late","text":"You outscale him in extended duels — outside his R he can't catch you, and with crit plus lifesteal you win every sidelane once his ult is down."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge his Q Obliterate and E pull","Survive his R realm on Undying Rage","Out-sustain his DoT after items"],"foe":["Land Q-E pull combo with shield up","Isolate you in R Realm of Death","Ramp passive damage in extended trades"]},"early":"Level 1 favours you — Morde is slow and clunky before his combo comes online, so trade with Q Bloodlust resets and shove him off the wave. Deny his passive Indestructible shield from stacking early.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are Mordekaiser's window: his Q Obliterate into E Death's Grasp pull with a full passive shield wins extended trades, and at 6 his R Realm of Death isolates you where lifesteal and escape don't save you. Sidestep the Q, avoid the E pull, and never fight him low at 6.","late":"From your first item you swing it back — bait his R, ride out the realm on Undying Rage, then out-sustain his DoT with Q once he's on cooldown. Late you outscale him: outside his ult he can't catch you, and crit plus lifesteal wins every sidelane duel.","whys":["Level 1 favours you — a clunky pre-combo Morde loses the Q-reset trade before his shield stacks.","Level 2 is even as his Q-E combo starts forming and threatens a real trade.","Level 3 stays a skill window between his shielded poke and your trade discipline.","Levels 4-5 favour Mordekaiser — his Q-E pull with full passive shield wins extended trades.","Level 6 stays his: R Realm of Death isolates you where lifesteal and escape don't save you.","At first item you flip it — surviving his R on Undying Rage lets your Q out-sustain his DoT.","Late you outscale him because outside his ult he can't catch a crit-lifesteal diver."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"nasus","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Nasus"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Your only job is to deny Nasus stacks: sit on his caster minions and E Spinning Slash in to slap him off his last-hit whenever his Q Siphoning Strike is down, since interrupting a stack is worth far more than the poke damage. He has no way to punish you back until 6, so trade freely and shove so he has to walk up under tower."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R Undying Rage lands before his fight tools matter, so this is your fattest window: all-in when his W Wither is on cooldown and burst him before he can slow-kite you, then Q Bloodlust the crit heal to reset. Every kill or Flash you force here delays his stack timing and is the game."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With early crit online you out-DPS an unstacked Nasus in a straight fight, so keep punishing and roam once you've shoved — a fed Nasus is only a problem if you let him farm in peace to his item spike."},{"when":"Late","text":"Once Nasus completes his tank items and a few hundred Q stacks, his Wither slow plus R Fury of the Sands armor lets him tank your crits and one-shot you back — avoid extended fights and split away from him, forcing side-lane pressure instead of dueling."}],"wants":{"you":["Deny Q Siphoning Strike stacks by contesting his last-hits","Fight while his W Wither is on cooldown","Snowball and end before he out-scales"],"foe":["Farm safely and hit hundreds of Q stacks","Land W Wither to kite your all-in","Drag the game to full tank items and R"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are even farming — Nasus can't punish you and you can't kill him yet, so just secure CS and match his shove without taking free harass.","mid":"From 3 to 6 it's a skill test of stack-denial: your job is to E in and cancel his Q Siphoning Strike animation on caster minions whenever it's up, keeping his stacks low while he has no answer until Wither and R come online.","late":"After your first crit item you win any short fight against an unstacked Nasus, but this flips hard late — his Wither, tank stats and stacked Q let him survive your R and kill you, so close the game or split before then.","whys":["Level 1 is a neutral farming start where neither of you threatens a kill.","Level 2 stays even — Nasus has no engage and you lack the tools to commit yet.","Level 3 is skill-based: your stack-denial pressure trades against his need to just farm.","Levels 4-5 remain a skill window as you contest stacks while he has no punish.","At 6 your R all-in beats a Nasus whose Wither and stacks aren't yet enough to survive.","After your first crit item you out-DPS an unstacked Nasus in a straight duel.","By 2+ items Nasus's tank stats, Wither slow and stacked Q let him tank your R and kill you."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"nautilus","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Skill","Nautilus","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is Nautilus's window: his Q Dredge Line hook plus passive AA root and W Titan's Wrath shield make his level-3 all-in genuinely scary, so respect the hook range and don't walk into minion-blocked spots where his Q connects cleanly. Farm from max range and only commit a trade after his Q is on cooldown, since a landed hook chains enough CC to kill you outright."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R Undying Rage flips the matchup — his hook combo can no longer burst you through the immortality window, so you can bait his Q, pop R if it lands, and Q Bloodlust back to full. Play for this: once you have R, his CC just delays a fight you win."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With crit online you out-scale a support-item Nautilus hard; keep shoving and roam, because he has no waveclear to punish your absence and no way to duel you once your R covers his CC chain."},{"when":"Late","text":"Nautilus stays relevant only as a peeling engage tank — avoid eating a fresh Q into R Depth Charge when your Undying Rage is down, but in any fight where R is up, you win the duel and can dive his carries."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Q Dredge Line and farm at range","Save R Undying Rage to survive his CC chain","Scale to crit items and out-duel him"],"foe":["Land Q hook into full CC combo at 3-5","Kill you before your R comes online","Use his tankiness to peel and disengage"]},"early":"Level 1 favours you — Nautilus is a slow, low-damage laner with no way to threaten you before he has his combo, so take free CS and deny his approach.","mid":"Levels 2 through 5 are a skill test around his Q Dredge Line: land your last-hits from range and never get caught in a minion wave where his hook plus passive root and Titan's Wrath shield let him burst you at 3.","late":"Once you hit 6 and your first crit item, R Undying Rage neutralises his entire CC chain — bait the hook, survive, and kill him — and from there you scale away from a support-item tank who can't duel you.","whys":["Level 1 favours you: Nautilus is slow with no combo and can't threaten you yet.","Level 2 is skill-based as you dodge Q and he sets up his engage.","Level 3 is a skill window — his all-in is real but only if his hook lands.","Levels 4-5 tilt to Nautilus, whose Q-into-full-CC combo can kill you outright.","At 6 your R survives his CC chain, flipping the all-in in your favour.","With your first crit item you out-scale and out-duel a support-item Nautilus.","By 2+ items you win any fight where R covers his CC and can dive past him."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"neeko","win":["Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You dominate this stretch: Neeko is a squishy immobile mage whose only escape is passive Inherent Glamour disguise, so E in whenever her E Tangle-Barbs root is on cooldown and force crit trades she can't answer. Her Q Blooming Burst poke is real, so use Q Bloodlust to heal it off and keep the CS lead while pressuring her off the wave."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her R Pop Blossom needs a 1.5s wind-up, so the moment she channels it, E Spinning Slash out or pop R Undying Rage — she has no other burst that threatens you, and dodging her ult effectively removes her whole kill combo."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With crit online you delete Neeko in a single engage; the only thing to respect is her E root landing first, so wait it out or bait it before committing, then all-in and reset with your Q crit heal."},{"when":"Late","text":"Neeko is a teamfight burst mage, not a duelist — split away from her ult angles, dodge her R Pop Blossom and E Tangle-Barbs, and you out-duel her one-on-one every time your R is up."}],"wants":{"you":["E in when her E Tangle-Barbs is down","Dodge R Pop Blossom's wind-up","Heal Q Blooming Burst poke with Bloodlust"],"foe":["Land E Tangle-Barbs root to set up burst","Hit R Pop Blossom for the all-in","Poke you down with Q from range"]},"early":"Level 1 is even as both of you just farm, but Neeko has no way to threaten a squishy start against your sustain, so contest CS freely.","mid":"From level 2 through 5 you own the lane — Neeko is immobile and squishy, so E onto her whenever her E Tangle-Barbs root is on cooldown, out-trade with crits and heal her Q poke off with Bloodlust.","late":"Post-6 you still win: her only kill threat is the slow R Pop Blossom wind-up, which you dodge with E or negate with Undying Rage, and once you have a crit item you delete her the instant her root is spent.","whys":["Level 1 is an even farming start with no kill threat either way.","Level 2 favours you against an immobile, squishy Neeko with no punish.","Level 3 is yours — you E in and out-trade whenever her E is down.","Levels 4-5 stay in your favour as your crits beat her poke.","Level 6 is skill-based: her R Pop Blossom can burst you if you eat the wind-up.","With your first crit item you delete Neeko once her root is spent.","By 2+ items you out-duel a squishy teamfight mage every time R is up."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"olaf","win":["Olaf","Olaf","Olaf","Olaf","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Olaf hard-wins early: his Q Undertow axe slow plus W Vicious Strikes lifesteal and passive Berserker Rage attack speed let him win every extended trade, and if he picks up his thrown axe the slow refreshes so you can't kite out. Do not fight him level 1-5 — farm carefully, dodge the axe by moving perpendicular, and give ground rather than dying to his sustained DPS."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Even with R Undying Rage the fight is close, but his R Ragnarok makes him immune to your W Mocking Shout slow and gives him tenacity and armor, so don't force it — your ult stops you dying but doesn't guarantee you kill through his sustain. Play for even and farm to your item spike."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is where you take over: with your first crit item your burst finally out-paces his lifesteal, so now you can commit when his Q axe is on cooldown, kite him with W Mocking Shout, and Q Bloodlust the crit heal to win the war of attrition you lost early."},{"when":"Late","text":"Fully itemised you out-scale Olaf hard — your crit plus R immortality window beats his sustain, and you can split-push freely since he has no reliable gap-closer beyond the axe slow, which you sidestep."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive early and reach your first crit item","Kite with W Mocking Shout once R Ragnarok is down","Dodge Q Undertow to deny the slow reset"],"foe":["Win extended trades 1-5 with W lifesteal and attack speed","Land Q Undertow and pick up the axe to chain-slow you","Use R Ragnarok to ignore your slows and all-in"]},"early":"Levels 1 through 4 belong to Olaf — his Q axe slow, Berserker Rage attack speed and W Vicious Strikes healing crush you in any sustained trade, so respect him, dodge axes and just farm without committing.","mid":"At 5-6 it evens out: your R Undying Rage stops him executing you, but his R Ragnarok ignores your Mocking Shout slow, so avoid coin-flip all-ins and farm toward your item spike instead.","late":"From your first crit item onward the matchup flips your way — your burst out-races his lifesteal, you kite him with Mocking Shout when Ragnarok is down, and by full items you out-duel and out-split a low-mobility bruiser.","whys":["Level 1 is Olaf's: his attack speed and axe slow win the first trade.","Level 2 stays Olaf's as his sustained DPS and lifesteal beat you.","Level 3 favours Olaf, who chain-slows with Q and out-heals you.","Level 4 still belongs to Olaf's superior early trading.","Level 5-6 evens out — your R stops the execute but Ragnarok ignores your slow.","Your first crit item flips it: your burst finally out-paces his lifesteal.","By 2+ items your crit and R window out-duel and out-scale him."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"ornn","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Skill","Ornn","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ornn's power spike is level 4 with both Q Volcanic Rumble and E Searing Charge up: his E dash can knock you up into a Q Brittle detonation for a big chunk, so respect the E range and don't stand in his Q flame pillar. Farm at range, dodge the E charge, and only trade when his abilities are down since his tank stats mean you lose short auto exchanges into his cooldowns."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R Undying Rage beats his single-target burst — bait his E Searing Charge and Q Brittle combo, survive it with R if needed, then Q Bloodlust the crit heal and turn. He has no execute, so once you have your ult his combo just sets up a fight you win."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With crit online you out-DPS an Ornn who builds pure tank; commit when his E is on cooldown, kite the Brittle setup, and reset with Bloodlust. He can't kill you, so this is your window to snowball or roam."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late-game Ornn is a scaling teamfight monster: his R Call of the Forge God global charge and second-cast knock-up plus his upgraded items make him tanky and dangerous in groups, so avoid grouped fights near him and split — one-on-one with R up you still edge the duel, but never eat a full R combo."}],"wants":{"you":["Fight when his E Searing Charge is on cooldown","Survive the Brittle combo with R Undying Rage","Out-scale a pure-tank Ornn with crit"],"foe":["Land E-into-Q Brittle detonation at level 4","Use tank stats to win short trades","Scale to R Call of the Forge God teamfights"]},"early":"Level 1 favours you before Ornn has his combo — take free CS and deny his flame-pillar zoning while he's weakest.","mid":"Levels 2-3 are a skill test, then level 4 tilts to Ornn: with Q and E up his E Searing Charge knock-up into a Q Brittle detonation is a real burst, so dodge the dash and only trade into his cooldowns.","late":"From 6 and your first crit item you take over — R Undying Rage survives his combo and your crits out-DPS a pure-tank Ornn — but by full items his teamfight R and upgraded tankiness make grouped fights his, so split and only duel him when your ult is up.","whys":["Level 1 is yours: Ornn lacks his combo and can't punish you yet.","Level 2 is skill-based as Ornn assembles his kit.","Level 3 stays a skill window before his spike lands.","Level 4 favours Ornn, whose E-into-Q Brittle combo bursts you.","At 6 your R survives his combo and lets you turn the fight.","Your first crit item lets you out-DPS a pure-tank Ornn.","By 2+ items Ornn's scaling teamfight R and tankiness make it even again."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"pantheon","win":["Skill","Pantheon","Pantheon","Pantheon","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Pantheon owns this window: his Q Comet Spear poke chunks you from range, his W Shield Vault stun sets up a full combo, and his passive Mortal Will empowers his Q or E for a big spike every few abilities. Don't walk into Q range at low HP, respect the W stun as his all-in starter, and farm defensively — every trade he initiates with W plus empowered Q beats you before your crit online."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R Undying Rage is your equaliser — his combo can no longer execute you, so bait the W Shield Vault stun, survive with R if it lands, and Q Bloodlust the crit heal to turn. His burst is front-loaded, so once your ult negates it the kill pressure flips to you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With crit you out-scale Pantheon hard; his early-game lead means nothing once your items come online, so commit when his W stun and Q are down, kite with Mocking Shout, and reset with Bloodlust. Force fights past the point his poke matters."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late Pantheon is a roaming assassin, not a duelist — one-on-one with your R up you win every time, so punish him in side lane and dodge his R Grand Starfall engage angle, then delete him with crits."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive early poke and reach 6 plus first item","Bait the W Shield Vault stun then all-in","Out-scale his front-loaded burst with crit"],"foe":["Poke with Q Comet Spear before you scale","Land W stun into empowered combo at 2-4","Kill you before R Undying Rage comes online"]},"early":"Level 1 is even before Pantheon's combo comes online, so farm safely and don't feed his Q Comet Spear poke.","mid":"Levels 2 through 4 belong to Pantheon: his empowered Q poke and W Shield Vault stun into a full combo out-trade you badly, so play defensively, dodge the spears and never contest a trade while his stun is up.","late":"At 5 it evens as you approach 6, and from your ult plus first crit item onward you flip the lane — R Undying Rage negates his front-loaded burst and your crits out-scale a squishy assassin you out-duel one-on-one.","whys":["Level 1 is even before Pantheon assembles his combo.","Level 2 favours Pantheon as his empowered poke and stun come online.","Level 3 belongs to Pantheon's W-stun all-in and Q poke.","Level 4 stays Pantheon's — his front-loaded burst out-trades you.","Level 5 evens out as you near your R spike.","Your first crit item flips it: R negates his burst and you out-scale.","By 2+ items you out-duel a squishy assassin whenever R is up."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"poppy","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Tryndamere","Poppy","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Level 4 is Poppy's window: with W Steadfast Presence up she negates your E Spinning Slash dash and knocks you down mid-cast, and her E Heroic Charge stun into a wall is a hard punish, so never E toward her while her W is active. Otherwise you win the earlier levels by trading with crits when her E is on cooldown and healing her Q poke off with Q Bloodlust."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R Undying Rage beats her — bait her E Heroic Charge and W into your ult window, survive, and Q Bloodlust the crit heal to turn. Just be careful of her R Keeper's Verdict knocking you away to deny a kill; it doesn't burst you, so eat it and re-engage."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With crit online you out-DPS Poppy in any straight fight; commit when her E stun and W are down, kite with Mocking Shout, and reset with Bloodlust. She has no way to duel you once you can't be dashed into a wall."},{"when":"Late","text":"Poppy is a peel-and-engage tank late, not a duelist — one-on-one with R up you win every time, so avoid grouped fights where her W denies dashes and E stuns you, and punish her in side lane instead."}],"wants":{"you":["Trade with crits when her E Heroic Charge is down","Avoid E-dashing into her W Steadfast Presence","Out-scale her with crit items"],"foe":["Land E Heroic Charge stun into a wall","Use W to negate your E dash at level 4","Peel and disengage with R Keeper's Verdict"]},"early":"Level 1 favours you before Poppy has her stun — take free CS and trade freely against a champion who can't punish you yet.","mid":"Level 2 is a skill test, level 3 is yours, but level 4 tilts to Poppy: her W Steadfast Presence cancels your E Spinning Slash dash and her E Heroic Charge stun into a wall is a real punish, so hold E and fight only when her stun is down.","late":"From 6 and your first crit item onward you dominate — R Undying Rage survives her combo, her R Keeper's Verdict only displaces you rather than killing you, and your crits out-DPS a peel tank you out-duel whenever your ult is up.","whys":["Level 1 is yours before Poppy has her stun to punish you.","Level 2 is skill-based as Poppy sets up her kit.","Level 3 favours you: you out-trade her with crits.","Level 4 tilts to Poppy, whose W denies your E and E stuns you into a wall.","At 6 your R survives her combo and lets you turn the fight.","Your first crit item lets you out-DPS Poppy in a straight fight.","By 2+ items you out-duel a peel tank whenever R is up."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"quinn","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Quinn","Skill","Quinn","Quinn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Your all-in threat exists but Quinn's Blinded Vault (E) dashes back off you and her Harrier (passive) procs chunk you every few autos, so trades stay roughly even unless she wastes E."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"You get R Undying Rage to survive her burst, but Quinn's ultimate Behind Enemy Lines (R) lets her roam and snowball map pressure you can't answer while you shove."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Quinn spikes hard on first item — her ranged poke plus Vault knockback kite your Spinning Slash (E) reset, and she out-DPS's you from range as an ADC-in-lane."},{"when":"Late","text":"You want to be split-pushing and forcing 1v1s, but Quinn's mobility and repeated E knockback make her one of the cleaner kiters against your melee crit windows."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait her E Vault out, then commit your Spinning Slash gap-close and Mocking Shout slow","Dodge Harrier procs by not sitting on the caster minion she marks","Roam or crash waves to punish her leaving lane to use R"],"foe":["Land Blinding Assault (Q) then autoattack you while blind cuts your damage","Vault (E) off you the instant you E in, resetting the trade","Use ranged Harrier poke to keep you low so you can't sustain with Bloodlust"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are even and reads as Skill — she has no strong all-in and you have no gap-closer yet, so it's a farm lane where landing Harrier procs vs dodging them decides small trades.","mid":"Level 3-5 stays skill-based, but at 6 Quinn flips ahead: she gets Behind Enemy Lines to roam and generate leads while your R only buys you personal survival, not tempo.","late":"On items and beyond Quinn is favoured — her ranged DPS, Vault knockback, and roam pressure kite your crit all-ins, so you must win by split-pushing rather than dueling her head-on.","whys":["Level 1 is even skill — neither of you has a committal tool and it's a pure farm/poke read.","Level 2 stays even skill — one point in an ability isn't enough for either side to force a decisive trade.","Level 3 is still skill — you can threaten an all-in but her Vault (E) knockback keeps it even.","Level 4-5 favours Quinn — her ranged Harrier poke and Vault kite let her win extended trades before you spike.","Level 6 is even skill — your R Undying Rage nullifies her burst, keeping the direct duel balanced.","First item favours Quinn — her ADC-style scaling and Vault knockback out-trade and kite your melee crit windows.","Two-plus items favours Quinn — ranged DPS plus roam mobility let her sidestep your all-ins and pressure the map."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"renekton","win":["Skill","Renekton","Renekton","Renekton","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is Renekton's window: with full fury he chains Ruthless Predator (W) stun into Cull the Meek (Q) and Slice/Dice (E) to burst you before your crits scale, so respect his fury bar."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R Undying Rage flips the fight — even a fully-fed Renekton dive can't finish you through it, and you heal back up with Bloodlust (Q) crits while your R timer runs."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You spike ahead: with Battle Fury crit chance and lifesteal your sustained DPS overtakes his empowered burst, and once his W stun is on cooldown he can't peel you off."},{"when":"Late","text":"Renekton falls off hard while you scale — your split-push and R make you the stronger 1v1 and duelist once his early kit stops one-shotting."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive the level 3-5 fury window, then trade back once his W is down","Use R Undying Rage to bait his dive, then Bloodlust-crit back to full","Space so his empowered W stun whiffs before you commit Spinning Slash"],"foe":["Hit you with the empowered Ruthless Predator (W) stun to lock in his combo","Play the early levels aggressively while he out-stats you with fury","Slice/Dice (E) reset to catch you and extend his short burst window"]},"early":"Level 1-2 is even skill — Renekton wants fury and levels to spike, and with only one or two points neither side commits, so it's a careful farm read.","mid":"Levels 2 through 5 belong to Renekton: empowered W stun plus Q healing and E mobility let him win every short trade and threaten kills before your crit scaling arrives.","late":"From level 6 on you take over — R Undying Rage neutralizes his all-in, and once your first item lands your sustained crit DPS and split-push outclass his fading early power.","whys":["Level 1 is even skill — no fury, no gap-closer, just farming and positioning.","Level 2 favours Renekton — his empowered W stun and Q sustain win the first real trade.","Level 3 favours Renekton — the full W-Q-E combo bursts you before your crits matter.","Level 4-5 favours Renekton — his fury-fueled trades and E resets keep him ahead in the kill window.","Level 6 is even skill — your R Undying Rage cancels his dive, balancing the direct fight.","First item favours Tryndamere — crit and lifesteal push your sustained DPS past his burst.","Two-plus items favours Tryndamere — you scale and split while Renekton falls off in the 1v1."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"riven","win":["Riven","Riven","Riven","Riven","Riven","Skill","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Riven owns this window — her Broken Wings (Q) chain, Ki Burst (W) stun, and Valor (E) shield let her all-in you repeatedly before your crits scale, and her mobility dodges your Spinning Slash."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Riven still edges you here — her Blade of the Exile (R) plus Wind Slash gives a burst execute that beats your health bar even with R up, so you survive but can't win the trade yet."},{"when":"1st item","text":"The lane evens to Skill: your Battle Fury crit and lifesteal close the gap on her early lead, and if she over-extends her Q chain you Spinning Slash in and punish the cooldown gap."},{"when":"Late","text":"You take over — once items land your sustained crit DPS and R survivability beat her cooldown-reliant burst 1v1, and your split-push pressure outscales her."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive her level 1-5 all-in bully phase and farm safely under tower","Bait her Q chain and E shield, then Spinning Slash in during her cooldown window","Use R Undying Rage to eat her full combo plus Wind Slash and heal back"],"foe":["Chain Broken Wings (Q) with Ki Burst (W) stun to burst you early","Use Valor (E) shield and dashes to dodge your Spinning Slash and Mocking Shout","Snowball the level 1-5 lead before your crit scaling comes online"]},"early":"Levels 1 through 5 belong to Riven — her Q mobility, W stun, and E shield let her all-in you on repeat before your crits matter, so you play safe, give ground, and just farm.","mid":"Through level 6 Riven stays ahead: her R execute plus Wind Slash burst still beats your health bar, so R Undying Rage keeps you alive but doesn't yet let you win the trade.","late":"By first item the lane evens and on two-plus items you flip ahead — sustained crit DPS, lifesteal, and R outclass her cooldown-dependent burst in the 1v1, and your split-push pressures the map she can't match.","whys":["Level 1 favours Riven — her early Q trade and mobility bully you before you have tools.","Level 2 favours Riven — Ki Burst (W) stun added to her Q chain wins every trade.","Level 3 favours Riven — the full Q-W-E combo all-ins you well before your scaling.","Level 4-5 favours Riven — she keeps snowballing the kill pressure while your crits lag.","Level 6 favours Riven — her R execute and Wind Slash burst still out-trade you even through your ult.","First item is even skill — your crit and lifesteal close the gap and punish her cooldowns.","Two-plus items favours Tryndamere — sustained DPS and R survivability beat her burst 1v1."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"rumble","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Skill","Rumble","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Rumble's spike arrives with Danger Zone heat — overheated Flamespitter (Q) plus Scrap Shield (W) speed and Electro Harpoon (E) slow let him zone you and chunk your approach before your crits ramp."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"You take back control: R Undying Rage lets you dive through his Equalizer (R) ult without dying, and once you're on him with Mocking Shout slow he can't kite in melee range."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You spike ahead — Battle Fury crit and lifesteal let you facetank Flamespitter and sustain through his poke, and his short-range Q means once you Spinning Slash in he's yours."},{"when":"Late","text":"You outscale — your split-push and R survivability beat a squishy Rumble 1v1, and dodging his Equalizer with R or E means his only real teamfight tool is wasted on you."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait or wait out his overheat, then Spinning Slash in during his cooldown","Facetank Flamespitter with lifesteal once you have Battle Fury crit","Use R Undying Rage to survive his Equalizer dive and stick with Mocking Shout"],"foe":["Manage heat to get an empowered overheated Flamespitter (Q) burst","Kite you with Scrap Shield (W) speed and Electro Harpoon (E) slow","Zone your approach and poke you down before your crit scaling arrives"]},"early":"Level 1 you're favoured — before Rumble builds heat his Q is weak and you can walk up and trade, using Bloodlust crits to win the early exchange while he has no burst yet.","mid":"Levels 2-3 even out as he gets heat management online, then at level 4-5 Rumble spikes: overheated Flamespitter, W speed, and E slow let him zone and poke you before you scale.","late":"From 6 onward you dominate — R Undying Rage negates his Equalizer dive, and once your first item lands your crit lifesteal facetanks his poke while your split-push outscales his squishy frame.","whys":["Level 1 favours Tryndamere — Rumble has no heat yet, so you win the early walk-up trade with Bloodlust crits.","Level 2 is even skill — he starts managing heat and neither side has a decisive edge.","Level 3 is even skill — his Flamespitter poke trades roughly with your farm and sustain.","Level 4-5 favours Rumble — overheated Q plus W speed and E slow let him zone and chunk you.","Level 6 favours Tryndamere — R Undying Rage lets you survive his Equalizer dive and stick to him.","First item favours Tryndamere — crit lifesteal facetanks his poke and his short-range Q can't stop your all-in.","Two-plus items favours Tryndamere — you outscale a squishy Rumble and split-push past his kite."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"ryze","win":["Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Skill","Tryndamere","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Level 3 evens out as Ryze gets his Overload (Q)-Rune Prison (E) root combo online, but at 4-5 you swing back — once you Spinning Slash in and Mocking Shout slow him, his short root can't peel your crits."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Ryze's Realm Warp (R) is a macro tool, not a duel button, so it does nothing to stop your all-in — R Undying Rage lets you dive through his burst and Bloodlust-crit him down."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You spike hard — Battle Fury crit and lifesteal let you sustain through his Q poke, and once you're on top of him his squishy mage body melts to your autos before mana costs let him kite."},{"when":"Late","text":"You outscale in the 1v1 — split-push and R make you the stronger duelist, and as long as you dodge his Rune Prison (E) root he has no way to survive your dive."}],"wants":{"you":["Walk up level 1-2 and trade with Bloodlust crits before his combo comes online","Dodge or bait Rune Prison (E) root, then Spinning Slash in and Mocking Shout slow","Facetank Overload poke with lifesteal once you have Battle Fury crit"],"foe":["Land Rune Prison (E) root then Overload (Q) and Spell Flux (W) burst","Poke you down with Q from range while kiting your approach","Use flux-empowered combos to chunk you before you close distance"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are yours — Ryze has no root combo yet and low base damage, so you walk up, trade with Bloodlust crits, and can threaten an early lead before he comes online.","mid":"Level 3 evens as his Q-E-W combo arrives, but by 4-5 you swing back: Spinning Slash and Mocking Shout let you stick past his short Rune Prison root and out-trade his squishy frame.","late":"Level 6 onward you're firmly ahead — his Realm Warp does nothing in a duel, R Undying Rage negates his burst, and crit lifesteal means you dive through his poke and kill him 1v1.","whys":["Level 1 favours Tryndamere — Ryze lacks his combo and you win the early walk-up trade.","Level 2 favours Tryndamere — still no root online, so your Bloodlust crits out-trade his weak poke.","Level 3 is even skill — his Q-E-W combo comes online and can root-burst if you misstep.","Level 4-5 favours Tryndamere — Spinning Slash and Mocking Shout let you stick past his short root.","Level 6 is even skill — his Realm Warp doesn't help in lane but his combo can still trade if you're careless.","First item favours Tryndamere — crit lifesteal facetanks his poke and melts his squishy body.","Two-plus items favours Tryndamere — you outscale and split while dodging his single root threat."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"sejuani","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Even lane — Sejuani is a tank with weak lane damage, so trades are decided by whether she lands Arctic Assault (Q) into Winter's Wrath (W); dodge her Q dash and it's a pure farm phase."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Still even: her Glacial Prison (R) stun is a real threat in a gank setup, but 1v1 she has no kill pressure on you, and R Undying Rage makes any tower dive on you fail."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You spike ahead — Battle Fury crit and lifesteal let your armor-shredding autos and true-damage crits chew through her tank stats faster than she can Frost Armor (passive) shield up."},{"when":"Late","text":"You outscale a tank 1v1 — split-push and R make you the win condition, and as long as you dodge her Q engage her Permafrost passive damage can't out-DPS your crits."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge her Arctic Assault (Q) dash to deny the W-Q lockdown","Farm evenly through the tank phase, then all-in once you have crit items","Use R Undying Rage to make any dive or gank on you fail, then crit back"],"foe":["Land Arctic Assault (Q) into Winter's Wrath (W) to lock you for a gank","Build Permafrost stacks so autos and Q apply bonus magic damage","Set up Glacial Prison (R) to let her jungler collapse on you"]},"early":"Levels 1-5 are dead even and read as Skill — Sejuani has almost no solo lane damage, so the phase is about dodging her Arctic Assault engage and farming cleanly rather than either side threatening a kill.","mid":"Through level 6 it stays even: her R stun matters for ganks, but in a straight 1v1 she can't kill you and your R negates any dive, so neither side gets ahead in lane alone.","late":"From first item on you pull ahead — crit, lifesteal, and armor shred let your autos melt her tank stats faster than her shields regenerate, and you become the scaling win condition she can't duel.","whys":["Level 1 is even skill — Sejuani has no lane damage and you have no gap-closer.","Level 2 is even skill — still a farm phase with only her Q engage to respect.","Level 3 is even skill — her W-Q combo can trade but has no kill threat 1v1.","Level 4-5 is even skill — the tank phase continues with neither side able to force a kill.","Level 6 is even skill — her R helps ganks but does nothing to win the direct duel.","First item favours Tryndamere — crit and armor shred out-DPS her tank stats and shields.","Two-plus items favours Tryndamere — you outscale a tank 1v1 and split-push as the win condition."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"sett","win":["Skill","Sett","Skill","Sett","Sett","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Sett's window — with Haymaker (W) shield-into-true-damage stored from Pit Grit (passive) punches and Knuckle Down (Q) slow, he wins every extended trade and can chunk you hard before your crits scale."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Sett still edges you: Facebreaker (E) grab plus The Show Stopper (R) suppress-slam is a real kill threat, and even with R Undying Rage he can trade you down and reset before your ult window ends."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You flip ahead — Battle Fury crit and lifesteal let your sustained DPS out-race his Haymaker, and once his E grab is on cooldown he has no way to peel you off in melee."},{"when":"Late","text":"You outscale — split-push and R survivability beat a tanky Sett 1v1, and dodging his Facebreaker (E) and R means his burst windows are wasted while your crits grind him down."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive the level 2-5 bully phase and farm without eating Haymaker","Bait his Facebreaker (E) grab, then Spinning Slash and Mocking Shout to punish","Wait for Battle Fury crit, then out-sustain his W with Bloodlust lifesteal"],"foe":["Store grit from punches, then unload Haymaker (W) true damage on your health","Land Facebreaker (E) grab into The Show Stopper (R) for a kill combo","Use Knuckle Down (Q) slow to stick and win extended early trades"]},"early":"Level 1 is even skill — before Sett stores grit his punches trade roughly with your Bloodlust crits, so it's a careful farm start. By level 2 he pulls ahead as Haymaker and his punch cadence come online.","mid":"Levels 2 through 5 belong to Sett: stored Haymaker true damage, Q slow, and at 6 the E-R combo give him kill pressure and win every extended trade before your crit scaling arrives.","late":"From first item on you take over — crit lifesteal out-sustains his Haymaker, and once his E grab and R are on cooldown your split-push and R survivability make you the stronger 1v1 duelist.","whys":["Level 1 is even skill — Sett hasn't stored grit yet, so early punches trade evenly with your crits.","Level 2 favours Sett — Haymaker comes online and his punch cadence wins the first real trade.","Level 3 is even skill — you can trade back briefly before his W is stored again.","Level 4-5 favours Sett — stored Haymaker and Q slow let him win every extended exchange.","Level 6 favours Sett — Facebreaker (E) into The Show Stopper (R) is a kill combo even through your ult.","First item favours Tryndamere — crit lifesteal out-sustains his Haymaker and beats his cooldowns.","Two-plus items favours Tryndamere — you outscale a tanky Sett 1v1 and split-push past his burst."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"shen","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Tryndamere","Shen","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once your Q is up you out-trade Shen hard: his Twilight Assault (Q) sword only shreds when it catches you, so bait it, walk out of the blade, then all-in when it's on cooldown and heal the return damage off minions."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Undying Rage flips any duel Shen thinks he wins with Spirit's Refuge (W) — pop R through his damage window, keep swinging, and Bloodlust heals you back to full before the invuln ends."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With crit online you shove and threaten the tower faster than Shen can farm, and his slow waveclear means you can zone him off CS between his Q uses."},{"when":"Late","text":"You out-splitpush Shen all game; the danger is his ultimate roam, so ping the second his R channels and either dive his now-Shen-less lane or collapse before he saves the fight."}],"wants":{"you":["Keep the wave shoving so you deny CS and pressure tower while Shen has no waveclear","Trade only when your Q Bloodlust is up so you heal the exchange","Track his global R and punish the lane he leaves"],"foe":["Land Twilight Assault (Q) on you and back it with Spirit's Refuge (W) to block your autos","Use passive shield and sustain to farm safely under tower","Roam with Stand United (R) to snowball other lanes since he loses the 1v1"]},"early":"Level 1-2 you can walk up and poke; Shen's only threat is his passive shield, so chip him and set the tempo before his Q comes online. Respect that his Q at 2 does real damage if it lands twice, so don't stand in the sword.","mid":"From level 3 you own the duel: bait Twilight Assault (Q), sidestep or wait it out, then all-in when it's down and heal through his Spirit's Refuge with Bloodlust. Level 6 you get Undying Rage, which hard-invalidates any window Shen picks — he simply can't kill you, and you keep hitting.","late":"With your first crit item you out-splitpush and out-DPS Shen in any prolonged fight. His entire late-game value is Stand United (R) roams, so ward for the channel and punish whatever he leaves undefended.","whys":["You favour L1 — Shen has no waveclear or Q yet, so you dictate the trade and CS.","Even at L2 — Shen's early Q shield-and-poke pattern trades roughly with your auto pressure.","You favour L3 — your Q heal beats his sustain and you can bait Twilight Assault then all-in.","Shen favours 4-5 — his Q+W combo and passive shield let him win short trades and farm safely.","You favour L6 — Undying Rage makes you unkillable through his damage while you keep swinging.","You favour first item — crit lets you out-shove and out-duel him before he can react.","You favour 2+ items — you out-splitpush and out-DPS Shen, whose only counterplay is his R roam."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"singed","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Skill","Singed","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is Singed's window: once he has Fling (E) plus Mega Adhesive he can flip you into his poison and your minions, so never chase him through the gas or you eat a Fling into a slow field and bleed out."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Undying Rage is your reset — if he Flings you and stacks poison, pop R and stay on him; Bloodlust out-heals his poison tick and you kill him before the invuln drops."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With crit you can burst Singed faster than his Poison Trail can whittle you, but only commit when his Fling is down — that cooldown is the whole matchup."},{"when":"Late","text":"You out-DPS and out-splitpush him; the trap is proxy-Singed running you around, so don't tunnel — take the free tower and CS he concedes instead of dueling in his poison."}],"wants":{"you":["Fight only when Singed's Fling (E) is on cooldown so he can't flip you into poison","Use Q Bloodlust to out-heal his Poison Trail during all-ins","Punish his low base damage after level 5 when you out-scale his sustain"],"foe":["Land Fling (E) into Mega Adhesive and drag you through his poison and your own minions","Proxy the wave to deny you CS and abuse your weak sidelane push early","Kite you endlessly with Poison Trail and movespeed so trades favour him"]},"early":"Level 1-2 you're fine to trade — Singed's poison ramps slowly and you can auto him without eating much. Don't overstay in the gas, but you set the early tempo before his Fling comes online.","mid":"Levels 3-5 belong to Singed: with Fling and Mega Adhesive he flips you into his Poison Trail and your creeps, so respect the flip and never facechase through the gas. Wait for Fling's cooldown to trade.","late":"From 6 on you take over. Undying Rage means his poison can never finish you, and Bloodlust out-heals the ticks while you swing. With crit items you out-DPS and out-splitpush him — just don't get baited into chasing proxy-Singed through his gas.","whys":["You favour L1 — Singed's poison ramps slowly and you can trade autos freely before his kit comes online.","Even at L2 — Singed farms with Poison Trail while you can't commit yet, roughly balancing the lane.","Even at L3 — his Fling is up but so is your Q heal; it's a skill check on not chasing through poison.","Singed favours 4-5 — Fling plus Mega Adhesive flips you into gas and minions for the trade he wants.","You favour L6 — Undying Rage negates his poison kill pressure and Bloodlust out-heals the ticks.","You favour first item — crit lets you burst him down faster than Poison Trail can grind you.","You favour 2+ items — you out-DPS and out-splitpush; his only tool left is running you around."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"sion","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Skill","Sion","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Sion's spike: a fully-charged Decimating Smash (Q) will knock you up and chunk you, so never sit in the wind-up — if he starts channeling, walk sideways out of the smash and only re-engage once it whiffs."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Undying Rage laughs at his combo — if Sion lands Q into Roar of the Slayer (E), pop R, keep swinging, and Bloodlust heals it all back before he can follow up."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With crit you shred his health bar faster than he can stack armour early; all-in when his Q is down and use W Mocking Shout to keep him from walking away."},{"when":"Late","text":"You out-splitpush Sion easily, but respect his passive — killing him spawns a raging zombie that can still hit hard, so back off during the death timer and disengage his ultimate freight-train."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge charged Decimating Smash (Q) and only commit when it's on cooldown","Use Q Bloodlust to heal through his poke and short trades","Splitpush and take towers since Sion can't answer your sidelane 1v1"],"foe":["Land a fully-charged Q knockup to set up a free trade or all-in","Poke you down with Roar of the Slayer (E) and stack armour to survive","Use Unstoppable Onslaught (R) to catch you or peel your dive"]},"early":"Level 1-2 you have the initiative — Sion's Q needs charge time and you can auto him between his last-hits. Don't stand in an obvious wind-up, but you set the tempo before his combo comes online.","mid":"Levels 3-5 Sion gets to threaten: a charged Decimating Smash (Q) into Roar of the Slayer (E) is a real chunk and can knock you up for his jungler. Sidestep the smash, wait out its cooldown, then trade with your heal advantage.","late":"From 6 you take over. Undying Rage nullifies any burst he lands, Bloodlust out-heals his poke, and with crit you out-DPS and out-splitpush him. Just respect his zombie passive on the kill and don't get caught by his charging R.","whys":["You favour L1 — Sion's Q needs charge time, so you win the early auto exchanges and dictate pace.","Even at L2 — Sion's poke and slow-build survivability roughly match your pressure before his combo.","Even at L3 — his charged Q threatens but your Q heal keeps trades even; it's about dodging the smash.","Sion favours 4-5 — a charged Q knockup into E poke gives him the trade and gank setup.","You favour L6 — Undying Rage negates his burst and Bloodlust heals the exchange.","You favour first item — crit shreds him faster than he stacks armour and you can lock him with W.","You favour 2+ items — you out-DPS and out-splitpush; his zombie passive is his only comeback tool."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"swain","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Tryndamere","Swain","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Swain's window is landing Nevermove (W) or a Vision of Empire (E) root to pin you in his Q — respect the root, and once he burns it, all-in while it's down and heal the poke off with Bloodlust."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Undying Rage hard-counters Demonic Ascension (R): when he pops ult to lifedrain and heal, pop R, stay on him, and out-sustain his drain — he can't kill you and you kill him first."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With crit you burst through Swain's health and shield faster than his R can heal it; commit when his E root is on cooldown and use W Mocking Shout to stop him kiting to his tower."},{"when":"Late","text":"You out-DPS and out-splitpush Swain in a sidelane 1v1; the danger is his teamfight — never dive into a Nevermove landing spot and disengage his R when he has minions to drain."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait or dodge Nevermove (W) and Vision of Empire (E) root, then all-in when they're down","Use Q Bloodlust to out-heal his poke and out-sustain his R drain","Splitpush and take towers since Swain can't win the 1v1"],"foe":["Land a root (W or E) to pin you for his Q and passive stacks","Poke you with Death's Hand (Q) and stack passive souls to snowball","Turn a committed fight with Demonic Ascension (R) to lifedrain back to full"]},"early":"Level 1-2 you can walk up and trade; Swain's poke is real but manageable and you set the tempo before his root threats come online. Don't feed him passive stacks by standing in his Q, but the initiative is yours.","mid":"Level 3 onward it's a root check: if Swain lands Nevermove (W) or Vision of Empire (E) he pins you for full Q damage. Bait the root, trade when it's down, and your Bloodlust heal keeps you ahead. Level 4-5 he's strongest with both roots and stacks up.","late":"From 6 you dominate. Undying Rage beats Demonic Ascension outright — he drains, you survive and out-sustain, then kill him. With crit you out-DPS and out-splitpush; just never walk into a Nevermove spot in a grouped fight.","whys":["You favour L1 — you out-trade Swain's early autos and set the pace before his roots are up.","Even at L2 — Swain's Q poke and passive stacking roughly balance the lane.","You favour L3 — your Q heal beats his poke and you can bait the root then all-in when it's down.","Swain favours 4-5 — both roots online plus passive stacks let him pin you and win extended trades.","You favour L6 — Undying Rage negates his R heal-drain and you out-sustain him to death.","You favour first item — crit bursts through his shield and heal faster than he can recover.","You favour 2+ items — you out-DPS and out-splitpush Swain, who can't win the sidelane duel."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"sylas","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Sylas","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You win these levels: Sylas leans on Kingslayer (W) to heal his trades, so bait the W, all-in when it's on cooldown, and your Bloodlust out-heals his Chain Lash (Q) poke while you shred him."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"This is Sylas's spike, not yours — he steals your Undying Rage with Hijack (R) and gains a free unkillable window, so don't force an even fight at 6; wait for his R cooldown before committing."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With crit back on your side you re-take the duel; punish the long Hijack cooldown by all-inning whenever his stolen ult is down and lock him with W Mocking Shout so he can't kite."},{"when":"Late","text":"You out-splitpush and out-DPS Sylas in a 1v1, but respect that he can steal a game-changing ult in teamfights — sidelane him and make him choose between your tower and the fight."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait Kingslayer (W) then all-in when his heal is down","Use Q Bloodlust to out-sustain his Chain Lash (Q) poke","Splitpush and force 1v1s where Sylas can't out-duel you"],"foe":["Hit level 6 and Hijack (R) your Undying Rage for a free unkillable window","Poke you with Chain Lash (Q) and heal trades with Kingslayer (W)","Use E dash-stun mobility to disengage your all-in and reset"]},"early":"Level 1-2 you have the edge — Sylas's early trades rely on his Q poke and you can walk up and auto him between casts. Set the tempo before his kit comes fully online.","mid":"Level 3-5 stays yours: bait Kingslayer (W), all-in when it's down, and your heal beats his poke-and-sustain pattern. He'll try to E away, so use W Mocking Shout to keep him in range while you swing.","late":"Level 6 is his one good window — Hijack steals your Undying Rage, so don't force an even fight there; wait out the long R cooldown. From your first crit item on you re-take the duel, out-DPS him, and out-splitpush. In grouped fights respect his ult theft, so sidelane him instead.","whys":["You favour L1 — you out-trade Sylas's early autos before his poke-heal pattern comes online.","Even at L2 — Sylas's Q poke and mobility roughly balance the lane.","You favour L3 — you can bait Kingslayer and all-in when his heal is down, out-sustaining his poke.","You favour 4-5 — your heal keeps beating his trades and W stops him escaping your all-in.","Sylas favours L6 — Hijack steals your Undying Rage for a free unkillable window on his terms.","You favour first item — crit re-takes the duel and you punish his long Hijack cooldown.","You favour 2+ items — you out-DPS and out-splitpush; his only edge is ult theft in teamfights."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"tahmkench","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Tahm Kench","Tahm Kench","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Tahm's window: with three Tongue Lash (Q) stacks he can proc a stun off his passive and eat your all-in, so never dive when you're at two grey-health stacks — walk out and reset the stack timer instead."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Undying Rage flips the matchup back to you — he can't burst you through R, and Bloodlust out-heals his passive grey-health regen while you swing him down before he can Devour (W) away."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With crit you out-DPS his tankiness and his passive shielding; commit when his Q stun is off or under three stacks, and use W Mocking Shout to stop him kiting to safety."},{"when":"Late","text":"You out-splitpush Tahm all day, but respect his Devour (W) and Abyssal Dive (R) roam pressure — ward for his global and don't tunnel into a fight where he can eat you or a teammate."}],"wants":{"you":["Avoid stacking three Tongue Lash (Q) marks so he can't stun your all-in","Use Q Bloodlust to out-heal his passive grey-health sustain","Splitpush and take towers since Tahm can't win the duel after 6"],"foe":["Land Tongue Lash (Q) three times to stun and win the trade","Farm safely behind his passive grey-health shield and armour","Use Devour (W) and Abyssal Dive (R) to disengage or roam onto other lanes"]},"early":"Level 1-2 you set the pace — Tahm's Q poke is annoying but his kit isn't online yet, so trade autos and keep him from getting comfortable. Just start watching your passive stack count.","mid":"Levels 3-5 are Tahm's: three Tongue Lash (Q) stacks proc his stun, and a stun into his sustain wins any trade you start, so don't all-in while you're marked. Wait for the stack to fall off, then commit.","late":"From 6 you take over. Undying Rage means he can't kill you, Bloodlust out-heals his grey-health regen, and with crit you out-DPS his tank stats and out-splitpush him. Respect his Devour and global R for roams, but the sidelane is yours.","whys":["You favour L1 — you out-trade Tahm's early autos before his stun setup comes online.","Even at L2 — Tahm's Q poke and grey-health sustain roughly balance the lane.","Tahm favours L3 — three Q stacks let him stun your all-in and win the trade.","Tahm favours 4-5 — his stun plus passive sustain and armour beat your commits while marked.","You favour L6 — Undying Rage negates his burst and Bloodlust out-heals his grey-health.","You favour first item — crit out-DPSes his tankiness and W stops him kiting away.","You favour 2+ items — you out-splitpush and out-duel Tahm; his edge is Devour and R roams."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"teemo","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Teemo","Skill","Teemo","Teemo"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is Teemo's zone: Blinding Dart (Q) shuts off your autos and passive crit, so bait the blind before you commit — if you all-in into an up Q, you whiff your whole combo and eat Toxic Shot poison for free."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Undying Rage buys you a kill window since he can't burst you through R, but his Noxious Trap (R) shrooms slow and poison you on the retreat, so path around obvious mushroom spots when you dive."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Teemo pulls ahead again with items — his Q blind uptime plus shroom control means every all-in you start can be blinded and kited, so only commit when Blinding Dart is on cooldown."},{"when":"Late","text":"Teemo out-scales this lane: his shroom network zones your splitpush and his blind negates your DPS on demand, so buy a sweeper, clear vision before you dive, and force him into flat ground where he can't kite."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait Blinding Dart (Q) before committing so your autos and crit land","Buy an early sweeper and Merc Treads to fight the blind and shrooms","All-in only when his Q is on cooldown and you can pin him with W"],"foe":["Blind you with Blinding Dart (Q) to negate your autos and passive crit","Kite you with movespeed passive and Toxic Shot poke while you're blinded","Control the map with Noxious Trap (R) shrooms to zone your splitpush"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are a skill check — Teemo will try to Q-blind and poke with Toxic Shot on every last-hit, so trade only when his Q is down and don't let his poison stack you out of lane.","mid":"Level 3-5 Teemo takes over: a well-timed Blinding Dart cancels your entire all-in and his movespeed lets him kite the follow-up, so you have to bait the blind first. Level 6 you get a small window with Undying Rage, but his shrooms punish sloppy dives.","late":"Teemo out-scales you. His blind uptime and shroom network let him negate your DPS and zone your splitpush on demand. Buy a sweeper, path around mushrooms, wear Merc Treads for the poison, and only fight him on open ground where he can't kite you with movespeed.","whys":["Even at L1 — it's a skill check on trading around his Q blind and poison.","Even at L2 — Teemo pokes with Toxic Shot but can't kill you; the lane stays a blind-timing check.","Even at L3 — his Q is threatening but baitable; even trades if you respect the blind.","Teemo favours 4-5 — Blinding Dart cancels your all-in and his movespeed kites the follow-up.","Even at L6 — Undying Rage buys a kill window that offsets his shroom and blind control.","Teemo favours first item — item power ramps his blind uptime and poke to kite your commits.","Teemo favours 2+ items — his shroom network and on-demand blind out-scale your splitpush DPS."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"trundle","win":["Trundle","Trundle","Trundle","Trundle","Trundle","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Trundle owns these levels: his Q Chomp bites a chunk of your AD onto himself and his passive/Frozen Domain heal keep him topped through your Bloodlust harass, so trading straight up into his sustain loses."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R Undying Rage is the great equalizer — even while Trundle out-sustains you, popping Undying Rage means his Subjugate (R) drain and Pillar of Ice zone can't actually finish you, letting you Q back to full."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once you complete crit and Trundle can no longer heal through your DPS, the matchup flips — your Spinning Slash resets and 100% crit chew through him faster than Chomp + Frozen Domain can recover."},{"when":"Late","text":"Split-push endgame is yours: Trundle wants to Pillar teamfights, but a fed Tryndamere sidelanes and forces him to answer, where your R and crit outduel his single-target drain."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach 2-3 crit items so his sustain can't out-heal you","Use Undying Rage to bait his Subjugate drain then Q back","Split-push and avoid grouped Pillar of Ice fights"],"foe":["Chomp your AD and stat-check you during levels 1-6","Fight inside Frozen Domain for the attack-speed/heal buff","Pillar of Ice to trap your Spinning Slash escape"]},"early":"Trundle wins the opening levels outright. His Q Chomp steals your attack damage and heals him, and his passive plus Frozen Domain sustain shrug off Bloodlust pokes, so do not sit in extended autos with him early — you will lose the stat check.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay Trundle-favoured because Chomp and his heals let him bully the wave and win any all-in that your Fury bar isn't full for. Farm safely, only committing when your R is up, and let Undying Rage soak his Subjugate so he wastes his big drain on an unkillable target.","late":"After your first crit item the matchup swings hard to you. Trundle can no longer heal through 100% crit and Spinning Slash resets, so you outduel him in the sidelane and drag him away from the Pillar-zoning fights his team wants.","whys":["Trundle's Chomp steals your AD and his early sustain wins the level-1 trade.","His passive heal keeps him ahead through your level-2 Bloodlust harass.","At 3 his Q plus Frozen Domain out-sustains anything you can dish out.","Levels 4-5 still favour Trundle's stat-check and drain-tank profile.","Even at 6 his Subjugate and heals out-value your all-in before crit.","First crit item flips it — his heals can't keep up with your DPS now.","With 2+ items your crit and R split-push overwhelm his single-target drain."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"urgot","win":["Urgot","Skill","Urgot","Urgot","Urgot","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Urgot dominates the mid-laning phase: his Purge (W) shreds you while he shields, and Corrosive Charge (Q) plus Disdain (E) let him poke and shove faster than you can profitably trade into his range."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Urgot's Fear Beyond Death (R) is a hard problem — if he drops you below the execute threshold his ult snaps you in and shrugs off Undying Rage timing, so respect the R line and don't fight at low HP even during your immortality window."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once you finish crit the matchup turns: your sustained autos and Spinning Slash resets beat his cooldown-gated damage, and you can dive onto him between Purge windows since he has no reliable escape."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game favours you decisively — Tryndamere splits and outduels a lone Urgot, whose R is far less scary once your crit and Q healing let you race his execute."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Corrosive Charge and sidestep the Disdain flip","Stack crit so your DPS beats his Purge windows","Avoid fighting below Fear Beyond Death execute HP"],"foe":["Kite you with Purge while shielded during levels 3-5","Land Corrosive Charge slow into Disdain to lock a trade","Bait Undying Rage then execute you with his R"]},"early":"Level 1 is a coin-flip skill test — neither of you commits hard, so trade carefully and last-hit. From level 3 Urgot takes over: his Purge shreds while his shield holds and his Corrosive Charge zones you off farm, so don't stand in his range for extended trades.","mid":"Levels 3-6 are Urgot's window. Purge plus the Disdain flip stat-checks you, and at 6 his Fear Beyond Death can execute you even through the tail of Undying Rage if you're low. Farm patiently, dodge his Q slow, and never all-in below his execute threshold.","late":"After your first crit item you take control. Your resets and Q sustain let you race his execute and dive between Purge cooldowns, and by 2+ items a fed Tryndamere simply outduels and out-splits a lone Urgot.","whys":["Level 1 is an even skill test before Urgot's kit comes online.","Level 2 stays neutral until his Purge and shield spike.","At 3 Purge plus his shield shreds you in every trade.","Levels 4-5 remain his — Corrosive Charge and Disdain out-poke you.","At 6 Fear Beyond Death threatens to execute you outright.","First crit item flips it as your DPS beats his cooldown windows.","With 2+ items your split and duel power overwhelm a lone Urgot."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"vayne","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Vayne","Skill","Vayne","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Roughly even early — you have more base damage and can all-in her, but her Tumble (Q) repositions your autos and Silver Bolts (W) true damage chunks you, so trades come down to whether you catch her against a wall."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Even-ish at 6: your Undying Rage lets you survive her Condemn (E) stun and Silver Bolts burst, but if she pins you to terrain with Condemn she can kite the whole immortality window and finish you after."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Vayne's spike arrives here — her first item plus Silver Bolts true damage shreds you regardless of your HP, and Tumble invisibility from Q into her ult makes her hard to pin down and out-DPS."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game is Vayne's: with items her true-damage kiting outpaces even your crit and Q heals, and Condemn keeps you off her, so avoid extended 1v1s and use your R to disengage rather than to chase."}],"wants":{"you":["Pin her against a wall so Condemn can't create distance","All-in early before her item spike outscales you","Use Undying Rage to survive Condemn burst then Q up"],"foe":["Kite with Tumble and stack Silver Bolts true damage","Condemn you into a wall to stun and reset spacing","Scale to items where true damage beats your heals"]},"early":"The opening levels are a skill matchup — you out-base her and can commit if she mispositions, but her Tumble reshuffles your autos and Silver Bolts true damage bleeds you fast. Look to trade only when you can corner her against terrain.","mid":"Through level 6 it stays roughly even. Undying Rage lets you eat her Condemn stun and Silver Bolts burst, but a wall-pin Condemn can kite your whole ult, so don't dive her into her own turret and punish only clean mispositions.","late":"From her first item onward Vayne takes over. Silver Bolts true damage ignores your HP and Tumble invisibility keeps her out of your Spinning Slash range, so late-game 1v1s favour her — use R to disengage and let your team peel rather than solo-chasing.","whys":["Level 1 is an even skill test between your base damage and her kite.","Level 2 stays neutral as neither spikes hard yet.","At 3 it remains a skill trade decided by wall positioning.","Levels 4-5 tip to Vayne as Silver Bolts true damage adds up.","At 6 your Undying Rage keeps it roughly even through her burst.","Her first item spike lets true damage shred you past your heals.","With 2+ items her true-damage kite outduels your crit outright."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"vladimir","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Vladimir"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You win the early game: Vladimir is weak and mana-starved before levels, and your Bloodlust autos plus early all-in punish him hard before Sanguine Pool (W) and Transfusion (Q) sustain come online."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Still yours at 6 — your Undying Rage lets you commit through his Pool escape, and you can force flashes or kills before Hemoplague (R) and item sustain make him tanky and slippery."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You keep the edge into your first crit item: your DPS and Spinning Slash resets out-race his Transfusion healing, and he can only Pool once every trade to survive."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game is Vladimir's — once he stacks Rylai's/health and AP, his Transfusion sustain and Pool immunity out-heal your crit and he scales into an unkillable AoE threat, so close the game before items."}],"wants":{"you":["All-in during levels 1-6 before he scales","Bait Sanguine Pool then Q back and re-engage","End the game before his AP/health item spike"],"foe":["Survive early with Pool and Transfusion sustain","Farm safely to his AP and Rylai's scaling","Out-heal your crit and kite you late with Pool"]},"early":"You own the opening. Vladimir is one of the weakest early laners — low base damage and reliant on Transfusion — so pressure him with Bloodlust autos and threaten all-ins before his sustain kicks in. Levels 2-3 are a skill window as he tries to stabilize, but the pressure is yours to keep.","mid":"Levels 4-6 stay favoured to you. Undying Rage lets you dive through his Sanguine Pool, and you can burn his Flash or take the kill before Hemoplague and item sustain arrive. Keep denying him CS and force short trades his Transfusion can't fully heal.","late":"After your first crit item you still edge him, but by 2+ items Vladimir flips it hard. His stacked health and AP make Transfusion out-heal your crit, Pool dodges your all-in, and he becomes a slippery AoE monster — so you must snowball a lead early and end before he scales.","whys":["Vladimir's weak early kit loses the level-1 trade to your autos.","Level 2 is a skill window as he scrambles to stabilize.","At 3 it stays even while his Transfusion barely sustains.","Levels 4-5 favour you — you punish before his sustain scales.","At 6 your Undying Rage dive beats his Pool and heals.","First crit item keeps you ahead of his Transfusion healing.","With 2+ items his AP/health sustain out-heals and outscales you."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"volibear","win":["Volibear","Volibear","Volibear","Volibear","Volibear","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Volibear rules the early lane: his Thundering Smash (Q) stun on the charge plus Frenzied Maul (W) sustain and passive attack speed stat-check you hard, so straight autos into him lose and eating a Q stun means a big chunk of your HP gone."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Volibear's Stormbringer (R) leap disables your turret and gives him a huge shielded all-in — even Undying Rage can be timed around, so respect his level-6 dive threat and don't fight when he has R up and you're low."},{"when":"1st item","text":"The matchup flips at your first crit item: his Maul healing can no longer keep up with 100% crit and Spinning Slash resets, and once you outscale his tanky bruiser stats you win the sidelane duel."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game is decisively yours — a fed Tryndamere splits and outduels Volibear whose damage falls off, dragging him away from the teamfights where his R and Q stun matter most."}],"wants":{"you":["Farm safely through levels 1-5 and dodge the Q stun","Reach crit so his Maul heal can't out-sustain your DPS","Split-push late and duel him away from his team"],"foe":["Land Thundering Smash stun to win the early all-in","Stack Frenzied Maul heals during extended trades","Use Stormbringer to dive you and disable your turret"]},"early":"Volibear owns the opening levels. His Q stun on the charge, W sustain, and passive attack speed stat-check you, so don't sit in autos with him — eating a Thundering Smash stun early hands him the trade. Focus on safe farming and giving ground.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay Volibear-favoured. His Maul heals win extended trades and at 6 Stormbringer lets him dive through your turret with a big shield. Play patient, keep your Fury bar and R ready as insurance, and only commit when he's used his engage.","late":"Your first crit item flips the lane hard. Volibear's heals can't survive 100% crit and your resets, and from 2+ items a fed Tryndamere out-splits and outduels him, forcing him off the fights where his stun and ult carry his team.","whys":["Volibear's Q stun and attack speed win the level-1 trade.","At 2 his Maul sustain keeps him ahead in every exchange.","Level 3 stays his as his kit fully out-stat-checks you.","Levels 4-5 remain Volibear's on sustain and damage.","At 6 Stormbringer's dive and shield out-threaten your all-in.","First crit item flips it — his heals can't beat your DPS now.","With 2+ items your split and duel power overwhelm him."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"warwick","win":["Warwick","Warwick","Warwick","Warwick","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Warwick out-sustains and out-trades you early: his Jaws of the Beast (Q) heals him for a chunk of damage dealt and his passive lifesteal ramps under 50% HP, so any extended auto war refills his bar faster than Bloodlust refills yours."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Roughly even at 6 — your Undying Rage neutralizes his Infinite Duress (R) suppression all-in since you can't die during it, letting you Q back up while he's committed, so this is your window to reset the trade."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first crit item swings it: once you can chunk him faster than Q lifesteal recovers, his sustain advantage collapses and Spinning Slash resets let you win the sidelane duel."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game is firmly yours — a fed Tryndamere out-crits Warwick's sustain and out-splits him, while his single-target R does little against your immortality window."}],"wants":{"you":["Farm safely through levels 1-4 and avoid long auto trades","Pop Undying Rage to nullify his Infinite Duress at 6","Stack crit so your DPS beats his Q lifesteal"],"foe":["Win extended trades with Jaws of the Beast healing","Fight you under 50% HP where his lifesteal ramps","Land Infinite Duress suppression to lock an all-in"]},"early":"Warwick owns the first four levels. His Q heals him for a portion of the damage and his passive lifesteal spikes hard once you're low, so grinding autos into him just tops him off — avoid the extended trade and farm safely, giving up a little CS rather than a big chunk of HP.","mid":"Level 5 evens out and 6 is your reset window: Undying Rage makes his Infinite Duress suppression a non-threat because you can't die during it, so bait the R, Q back to health, and punish him while his big cooldown is spent.","late":"From your first crit item on, the matchup is yours. Your crit and Spinning Slash resets chunk him faster than Jaws of the Beast can heal, and by 2+ items a fed Tryndamere out-splits Warwick and shrugs off his single-target ult with the immortality window.","whys":["Warwick's Q healing and lifesteal win the level-1 trade.","At 2 his sustain keeps him ahead in every exchange.","Level 3 stays his as Q lifesteal out-heals your harass.","Levels 4 remain Warwick's on ramping lifesteal.","At 5-6 your Undying Rage neutralizes his R, evening it out.","First crit item flips it — your DPS beats his Q lifesteal now.","With 2+ items your crit and split overwhelm his sustain."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"wukong","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Skill","Wukong","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Wukong spikes here: his Warrior Trickster (W) clone plus Nimbus Strike (E) gap-close and armor passive let him out-trade you, and the W stealth can dodge your all-in commit, so respect his level 3-5 kill pressure."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Yours again at 6 — your Undying Rage beats his Cyclone (R) knock-up all-in since you can't die during it, so you can bait the ult, Q back to full, and turn the fight once his big cooldown is burned."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first crit item takes the lane: your sustained DPS and Spinning Slash resets out-trade his cooldown-reliant burst, and once W is down he has no way to survive your commit."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game is clearly yours — a fed Tryndamere out-duels and out-splits Wukong, whose damage is front-loaded and falls off, while your crit and immortality window win every extended 1v1."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait the Warrior Trickster clone before committing","Pop Undying Rage to survive his Cyclone all-in","Stack crit so sustained DPS beats his burst"],"foe":["Use W stealth to dodge your all-in and reposition","Trade with E gap-close and armor passive at 3-5","Land Cyclone knock-up to burst you before you heal"]},"early":"Level 1 is yours — your base damage and Bloodlust autos out-trade Wukong before his kit comes online. Levels 2-3 even out as he gets Warrior Trickster and Nimbus Strike, so don't over-commit into a possible clone bait during that window.","mid":"Levels 4-5 belong to Wukong: his W clone, E gap-close, and armor passive out-trade you and the stealth dodges your all-in. But 6 flips back to you — Undying Rage nullifies his Cyclone knock-up since you can't die, so bait the ult, Q up, and punish the spent cooldown.","late":"From your first crit item on, the lane is yours. Your resets and sustained DPS beat his front-loaded burst, and once his W is on cooldown he can't survive your commit — by 2+ items a fed Tryndamere out-splits and out-duels him outright.","whys":["Your level-1 base damage and autos out-trade Wukong.","Level 2 evens as he picks up his clone and gap-close.","At 3 it stays a skill trade around his W bait timing.","Levels 4-5 favour Wukong's clone, E, and armor passive.","At 6 Undying Rage beats his Cyclone all-in, flipping it to you.","First crit item wins it as your DPS beats his burst.","With 2+ items your crit and split out-duel him decisively."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"yasuo","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Skill","Yasuo","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once you have Q stacks and E, you can weave Spinning Slash through his minions to close distance he can't windwall away from. Bait his Sweeping Blade (E) dash onto a wave, then all-in while it's down, since without it he can't juke your autos or peel."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your Undying Rage is the reason this bracket flips green: you can commit fully into his burst, ignore his combo, and Q back to full health while he has no way to reset the trade. Save R for when he tornado-knocks you up, then heal through the follow-up."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With a completed crit item you shred him before his Q3 tornado and Windwall (W) come back up. His Windwall blocks projectiles, not your melee autos, so it does nothing to stop your DPS once you're on top of him."},{"when":"Late","text":"You out-duel him repeatedly since R lets you survive his ult knockup combo; just don't get caught in a 5-man Last Breath setup. In a straight 1v1 sidelane you win almost every time with Q healing and unstoppable crit uptime."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait his Windwall (W) onto your autos, then re-engage once it's spent","Track his Sweeping Blade (E) dash and all-in when it's on cooldown","Save Undying Rage for his ult knockup, heal back with Q after"],"foe":["Stack his tornado and poke you before your crit spikes","Use Windwall to block your ignite-less pressure and reset trades","Roam or ult a caught-out ally rather than duel you straight"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 favour you: you shove and trade with Q stacks and autos while his passive shield and E dash aren't enough to punish you yet, and Windwall can't stop melee hits. Play for pressure and deny his early flow-shield resets.","mid":"By L3-5 things even out as he gets his full Q-tornado and Windwall online; his dash mobility lets him kite your Spinning Slash. Level 6 is his danger point on paper, but your R turns it into your window: commit through his knockup, survive, and Q back up.","late":"With items you dominate. A completed crit item plus Undying Rage means you can eat his entire combo, live through the knockup, and heal to full while chunking him. In sidelane 1v1s you almost never lose; only a coordinated 5v5 knockup chain threatens you.","whys":["Level 1 is yours because your Q-stacked autos and shove beat his weak early flow-shield before his combo comes online.","Level 2 is even skill since he gets a second ability but neither of you has a real all-in yet.","Level 3 is even as his full Q-tornado and Sweeping Blade dash let him kite, offsetting your E gap-close.","Levels 4-5 tilt to Yasuo because his tornado, Windwall, and dash uptime let him control spacing before your crit spike.","Level 6 flips to you: Undying Rage lets you commit through his ult knockup, survive, and heal back with Q.","At first item you out-scale him, shredding him before his tornado and Windwall reset.","With 2+ items your R plus crit uptime win nearly every straight duel against him."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"yone","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Tryndamere","Yone","Tryndamere","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Level 3 is a strong window for you: before his Q3 knockup is reliably stacked, weave E in and trade with Q-stacked autos. Bait his Spirit Cleave (W) shield, then punish the cooldown. Watch his Q2/Q3 dash-tornado, but between casts he has little to stop your melee DPS."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Yone's R Fate Sealed and his soul-Q from his ult combo make L4-6 his stretch; his double-dash (E return) lets him engage and safely disengage. Your Undying Rage covers his all-in, so save R for when he Fate-Seals you and heal through it with Q afterward."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Trades even out into item timings. He gets sustain and burst from crit/on-hit builds, so you can't simply outstat him early; look for picks when his E soul is on cooldown and he can't retreat to his marked position."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game is skill-dependent: his Fate Sealed can lock you during your crit windows, and his mobility lets him disengage losing trades. R keeps you alive through his combo, but he can reset and kite where Yasuo cannot, so respect his outplay tools."}],"wants":{"you":["All-in at L3 before his Q3 knockup is consistently stacked","Bait his Spirit Cleave (W) shield, then trade into the cooldown","Save R for his Fate Sealed (R), heal back with Q once it ends"],"foe":["Land Q3 knockup and E-return to trade then safely disengage","Use Fate Sealed (R) to lock you during your crit windows","Kite with double-dash mobility instead of committing to a duel"]},"early":"Level 1 is yours with Q-stacked auto pressure before his Q-tornado stacks and Spirit Cleave shield matter. Level 2 evens as he picks up his second ability. This is your cleanest window to build a lead before his dash-tornado combo comes online.","mid":"Level 3 swings back to you: your E all-in beats his kit before his Q3 knockup is reliable. But L4-6 belong to Yone, whose stacked Q3, E soul-return, and eventually R let him engage, trade, and disengage safely. Use Undying Rage to survive his ult, not to force a losing trade.","late":"Item and late phases are even and skill-based. His Fate Sealed can lock you exactly when your crits come online, and his double-dash mobility lets him kite or reset trades you'd win against a less mobile duelist. R saves you from his burst, but you must outplay his soul-return timing to actually close.","whys":["Level 1 is yours because Q-stacked autos out-pressure his weak pre-tornado early before his shield matters.","Level 2 is even skill as he gains a second ability but no committal all-in yet.","Level 3 is yours since your E all-in lands before his Q3 knockup is reliably stacked.","Levels 4-5 favour Yone as stacked Q3 and E soul-return let him engage and disengage safely.","Level 6 stays with Yone because Fate Sealed adds a lockdown ult on top of his mobility.","First item is even skill: his sustain and mobility offset your crit growth in trades.","With 2+ items it's skill-dependent, as his Fate Sealed and double-dash can neutralize your crit windows."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"yorick","win":["Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Skill","Skill","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once he has Maiden and full ghoul stacks, the lane evens out: his Last Rites (Q) empowered autos plus ghoul chip make raw trades bad for you. Kill ghouls with cleave autos when you must fight, but prefer to avoid extended trades while his Maiden is up and his W cage can wall off your escape."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Level 6 stays even because his Eulogy of the Isles (R) Maiden makes a straight duel a numbers loss even through your R. Don't all-in into a fresh Maiden; instead use your R to survive if he cages you with Dark Procession (W), then Q out and reset rather than trading blows with the ghoul swarm."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your crit item is the turning point: with lifesteal and crit you can burst him down faster than his ghouls and Maiden can whittle you, especially if you kill ghouls first. Split-push relentlessly, because you clear side waves and towers faster than he can answer."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game is yours: your DPS and Q sustain let you 1v1 through his Maiden once you have items, and your mobility makes you the better splitpusher and teamfight flanker. Force sidelane pressure and make him choose between defending and grouping."}],"wants":{"you":["Fight at L1-2 before his Maiden and ghoul stacks come online","Kill his ghouls with cleave autos before committing to him","Splitpush with crit items where you out-clear and out-duel him"],"foe":["Stack ghouls and summon Maiden (R) to win the numbers trade","Cage you with Dark Procession (W) to trap you in the swarm","Freeze and farm safely, denying you an all-in window"]},"early":"Levels 1 and 2 are clearly yours: before Yorick has ghoul stacks or Maiden, your Q-stacked autos and E gap-close punish him hard, and he has no way to answer your raw damage. Trade aggressively and deny his early stacking to start the lane ahead.","mid":"From L3 through 6 the lane evens: his Last Rites autos, ghoul chip, W cage, and eventually Maiden turn straight trades into a numbers loss. Kill ghouls before fighting, use R only to survive his cage-combo, and avoid all-inning a fresh Eulogy Maiden.","late":"Items flip it firmly your way. With crit and lifesteal you burst him faster than his ghouls and Maiden whittle you, and your mobility makes you the superior splitpusher and flanker. Take side waves, out-duel him once you kill the ghouls, and make him choose between his tower and his team.","whys":["Level 1 is yours because Q-stacked autos punish him before any ghoul stacks or Maiden exist.","Level 2 stays yours since your E all-in still lands before his summon economy comes online.","Level 3 is even as ghoul stacks and Last Rites autos start turning trades into a numbers game.","Levels 4-5 are even because his Maiden and W cage let his swarm out-trade you.","Level 6 stays even since a fresh Eulogy Maiden makes a duel a numbers loss even through your R.","At first item you pull ahead: crit and lifesteal let you burst him faster than his ghouls whittle you.","With 2+ items you out-duel and out-splitpush him thanks to DPS, sustain, and mobility."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"zac","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Skill","Zac","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Zac gets his full kit and passive blob sustain online here, so extended trades refill his health. Dodge his Stretching Strike (Q) and Elastic Slingshot (E) rather than facechecking; if he lands a Q-Q double grab you eat real damage. Look to punish the long cooldown on his E after he uses it to engage or roam."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Level 6 flips green: his Let's Bounce (R) is a teamfight/pick tool, not a 1v1 win button, and your Undying Rage lets you commit fully and Q back to health. Bait his Q and E, then all-in when both are down since he has no burst to punish your R."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With a crit item you out-damage his blob-regen and duel him cleanly once his Q and E are on cooldown. His sustain can't keep pace with crit plus lifesteal, so trade when his engage tools are spent and he can't peel you off."},{"when":"Late","text":"You beat him in a straight sidelane duel with R and crit uptime, but respect that his real value is engaging your team with R. Splitpush to force him to answer, and don't chase him into his jungle where an E-R engage sets up a gank."}],"wants":{"you":["All-in at 6 when his Q and E are on cooldown; R covers his damage","Dodge Elastic Slingshot (E) and punish its long cooldown","Splitpush with crit where sustain can't outpace your DPS"],"foe":["Land Q-Q double grab and refill via passive blobs in long trades","Engage your team with Let's Bounce (R) instead of dueling you","Use E to disengage losing trades or set up a jungle gank"]},"early":"Level 1 is yours: before Zac has his full kit and blob-passive sustain, your Q-stacked autos out-pressure his short-range Q pokes. Trade early and deny him free stacking. From L2 on he starts refilling health, so make your damage count while he's still fragile.","mid":"L2 through 5 even out as his passive blobs, Stretching Strike, and Elastic Slingshot come online and extended trades heal him back. Dodge his grabs rather than facechecking, and punish the long E cooldown after he engages. L4-5 is his best window with full sustain, so pick your fights.","late":"Level 6 and items flip firmly to you. His R is an engage tool, not a duel button, and your Undying Rage lets you commit through anything he has and Q back to full. With crit and lifesteal you out-damage his regen; splitpush to make him answer, but never chase into his jungle where E-R sets up a gank.","whys":["Level 1 is yours because Q-stacked autos out-pressure his weak early before blob sustain exists.","Level 2 is even as his passive blobs and Q start letting him heal through trades.","Level 3 stays even since his full Q and E kit lets him poke and refill health.","Levels 4-5 favour Zac because full blob sustain lets him win extended trades.","Level 6 flips to you: R is only an engage tool while your Undying Rage wins the all-in.","At first item you out-damage his regen with crit and lifesteal once his Q and E are down.","With 2+ items your R and crit uptime win the straight sidelane duel outright."]},
  {"a":"tryndamere","b":"ziggs","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is Ziggs' comfort zone and it plays even: his Bouncing Bomb (Q) poke out-ranges you and chips you down before you can close. Path through side-brush and minions to dodge Q, and respect his Satchel Charge (W) knockback plus his Hexplosive Minefield (E) slow-field which can zone your all-in. Don't walk into a full rotation with no minions to E through."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Level 6 stays even: his R Mega Inferno Bomb adds long-range wave-clear and burst, but your Undying Rage lets you survive a full poke burst and Q back up. Use R defensively to eat his combo, then commit once his W knockback and E field are on cooldown so he can't reset the spacing."},{"when":"1st item","text":"First item swings to you: with a crit item and boots you finally close the gap through his E field and W, and once you're on him his short cooldowns don't save him. He has no reliable self-peel besides the W bump, so a clean E-in past his zoning is usually a kill."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game is yours in a sidelane: you gap-close and burst him before his poke matters, and R denies his burst. Beware roaming and teamfights where his long-range R and zoning shine, so splitpush to isolate him and force a 1v1 he can't win."}],"wants":{"you":["Path through brush and minions to dodge Bouncing Bomb (Q) poke","E in once his Satchel (W) and Minefield (E) are on cooldown","Splitpush to isolate him into a 1v1 his poke can't win"],"foe":["Zone your all-in with Hexplosive Minefield (E) and Q poke","Bump you away with Satchel Charge (W) to reset spacing","Use R and long range to poke and wave-clear from safety"]},"early":"The whole early game is even and skill-based: Ziggs' Bouncing Bomb out-ranges your autos and chips you every time you step up, but you can dodge it by pathing through brush and minions. Deny his free poke, take short trades when his Q is down, and don't over-extend into his E field with no escape.","mid":"L3 through 6 stays even. His W knockback, E slow-field, and eventually R zoning let him hold you at range, and a full rotation hurts if you facecheck it. Use Undying Rage to survive his burst, not to force through his zone; commit only once his W and E are spent so he can't reset the gap.","late":"Items flip it to you. A crit item and boots let you close through his zoning, and once you're on top his short cooldowns and lack of self-peel mean he dies fast, with R covering any burst. Splitpush to isolate him into a 1v1 his poke can't win, but respect his long-range R and zoning in grouped fights.","whys":["Level 1 is even skill because his Q out-ranges you but you can dodge it through brush and minions.","Level 2 stays even as his poke chips you but he has no all-in threat yet.","Level 3 is even since his W and E zoning offset your attempts to close.","Levels 4-5 remain even with his full poke-and-zone kit holding you at range.","Level 6 is even because his R adds burst but your Undying Rage lets you survive it.","At first item you pull ahead: crit and boots let you gap-close through his zoning and burst him.","With 2+ items you isolate and kill him in a sidelane his poke can't defend."]}
